data.cause: Clean up of the resources registered in CRSD started.
data.action: None\n

data.message: The clean up of the CRSD resources failed.
data.cause: Clean up of the resources registered in CRSD failed.
data.action: Check the CRS alert log.\n

data.message: Clean up of CRSD resources finished successfully.
data.cause: Clean up of the resources registered in CRSD finished.
data.action: None\n

data.message: The CSS daemon is terminating due to a fatal error; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: A fatal error occurred during CSS daemon processing.
data.action:
Check for prior errors logged in the alert log. Correct any
errors that can be corrected.  If there are no errors shown,
or the errors cannot be resolved, contact Oracle support

data.message: Unable to obtain the voting file discovery string; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: An attempt to obtain the voting file discovery string from\nthe profile failed, causing the CSS daemon to fail.
data.action:
Collect the Clusterware alert log and the CSSD log of this
node as well as all CSS daemon logs of all other nodes in the
cluster and contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: There is a mismatch of the initial cluster incarnation among the cluster nodes; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: An internal error occurred.
data.action:
Collect the Clusterware alert log and the CSSD log of this
node as well as all CSS daemon logs of all other nodes in the
cluster and contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: An attempt to kill node %s failed; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: To protect data integrity a node kill was attempted for\nthe indicated node, but it failed.
data.action:
Collect the Clusterware alert log and the CSSD log of this
node as well as the CSS daemon logs of all other nodes in the
cluster and contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: The CSS daemon shutdown has completed
data.cause: A command to shut down the CSS daemon was issued by a user\nand the shutdown processing is completed.  The CSS daemon\nis terminated.
data.action: No action is required.\n

data.message: The CSS daemon is not responding. Reboot will occur in %d milliseconds; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: The CSS daemon is failing to respond.
data.action:
Collect the Clusterware alert log and the CSSD log of this
node as well as the CSS daemon logs of all other nodes in the
cluster and contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Member kill requested by node %s for member number %d, group %s
data.cause: A request to kill a member of the indicated group\nwas issued by a process on the indicated node.
data.action: No action is required.\n

data.message: Member kill issued by PID %s for %d members, group %s. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: A member kill request was issued by the indicated process\nfor the members belonging to the indicated group.
data.action: No action is required.

data.message: No voting files found; switching node role to 'leaf'.
data.cause: A node attempting to start as a Hub node was not able to find a voting file.
data.action: No action is required.

data.message: maximum number of cluster Hub nodes reached; the CSS daemon is terminating
data.cause: A node attempting to start as a Hub node found the maximum number\nof Hub nodes already active.
data.action:
If the configured node role is 'auto', no action is required
for the node to restart as a Leaf node.  If the configured
node role is 'hub', then the configured role must be changed
to a Leaf node using 'crsctl set node role leaf' or the Hub size
must be increased using 'crsctl set cluster hubsize'.

data.message: no Hub nodes found; switching node role to 'hub'
data.cause: A node attempting to start as a Leaf node was unable to locate any Hub nodes.
data.action: No action is required.

data.message: node %s not allowed to join because the maximum number of Hub nodes has been reached
data.cause: A node attempting to start as a Hub node found the maximum number\nof Hub nodes already active.
data.action: No action is required.

data.message: operation is not allowed on a Leaf node\\n
data.cause: An unsupported operation was requested on a Leaf node.
data.action: Retry this operation on a Hub node.

data.message: The number of voting files available %d is less than the minimum number of voting files required %d.
data.cause: The number of voting files has decreased to a number of files\nthat is insufficient.
data.action: Look in the alert log for related messages such as 1714,\n1604, 1613, 1614 and 1615 and act accordingly.

data.message: Leaf node could not find any Hub nodes to connect to; details at %s in %s
data.cause: A Leaf node attempted to join the cluster but could not find a\nHub node to which to connect.
data.action:
Verify that the clusterware stack is up and running on at least
one Hub node and, if not, start the stack on one or more Hub nodes.
Verify that the Grid Naming Service (GNS) resource is active on a Hub node.
If not, start it on at least one node. Check if the network connectivity
is viable to all Hub nodes that have the clusterware stack running.
If the Leaf node startup has exhausted its retry attempts, it may be
necessary to start the clusterware stack manually on the Leaf node.
Contact Oracle Support Services if all of the above is verified
and the Leaf node is not able to find any Hub nodes to which to
to connect.

data.message: The value for parameter %s is outside the allowed range of %d to %d\\n
data.cause: An attempt was made to set a parameter with invalid value.
data.action: Set the parameter with a value in the indicated range.\n

data.message: The number of voting files currently available %d has fallen to the minimum number of voting files required %d.
data.cause:
The Cluster Synchronization Service daemon (CSSD) has detected that
the number of voting files currently available is equal to the
minimum number of voting files required on the node. There is risk
of node eviction in the case of another voting disk failure.
data.action:
Restore access to voting files or configure additional voting disks
so that the number of voting files currently available is
more than the minimum number of voting files required.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

data.message: Initialization of the required component GIPC failed; details at %s in %s
data.cause: The initialization of the communications component GIPC failed,\ncausing the CSSD startup to fail.
data.action: Collect alert log and the CSSD log indicated in the message\nand contact Oracle Support Services.\n

data.message: Initialization of the required component OLR failed; details at %s in %s
data.cause: The initialization of the local repository component OLR failed,\ncausing the CSSD startup to fail.
data.action: Collect clusterware alert log and daemon logs and contact\nOracle Support Services.\n

data.message: Initialization of the required component GPNP failed because the GPNP server daemon is not up; details at %s in %s
data.cause: The initialization of the configuration profile service failed\nbecause the associated server is not up, causing the CSSD\nstartup to fail.
data.action: Collect clusterware alert log and daemon logs and contact\nOracle Support Services.\n

data.message: Initialization of the required component %s failed; details at %s in %s
data.cause: The initialization of a component required by the CSS daemon\nfailed, causing the CSSD startup to fail
data.action: Collect clusterware alert log and daemon logs and contact\nOracle Support Services.\n

data.message: Found %d configured voting files but %d voting files are required, terminating to ensure data integrity; details at %s in %s
data.cause: The voting file discovery was unable to locate a sufficient\nnumber of valid voting files to guarantee data integrity and\nis terminating to avoid potential data corruption.
data.action:
Delete the voting files that are no longer available, as
indicated by message number 1637, using appropriate 'crsctl'
commands, run either on another node where the clusterware
stack is active, or by starting the clusterware stack in
exclusive mode.

data.message: error %d encountered when connecting to %s
data.cause: Connection to the target process failed.
data.action: Examine whether the connection is made properly.\nRetry again at a later time if necessary.

data.message: Found %d of %d voting files in a pending configuration change but %d voting files are required, terminating to ensure data integrity; details at %s in %s
data.cause:
The voting file discovery was unable to locate a sufficient
number of voting files from the new configuration when a
configuration change to add or delete voting files is in
progress.  The CSS daemon is terminating to avoid potential
data corruption.
data.action:
Delete the voting files that are no longer available, as
indicated by message number 1638, using appropriate 'crsctl'
commands, run either on another node where the clusterware
stack is active, or by starting the clusterware stack in
exclusive mode.

data.message: Lease acquisition for node %s number %d completed
data.cause: CSSD acquired a node number through a lease acquisition procedure.
data.action: None\n

data.message: Lease acquisition failed for node %s because all lease slots are in use; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: The node failed to acquire a lease because all the lease slots\nwere found to be occupied by other nodes.
data.action: Using olsnodes command get the list of leased nodes.\nDelete the unused nodes using appropriate crsctl command.\n

data.message: Lease acquisition failed for node %s because no voting file has been configured; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: At least one voting file is required for CSSD to function properly.\nNo voting files have been configured.
data.action: Add at lease one voting file using appropriate crsctl command.\n

data.message: Lease acquisition failed for node %s because CSSD failed to access majority of voting files; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: A majority of the voting files are not accessible by a node.
data.action:
Delete the voting files that are no longer available, as
indicated by message number 1637, using appropriate 'crsctl'
commands, run either on another node where the Clusterware
stack is active, or by starting the Clusterware stack in
exclusive mode.

data.message: Increasing the number of leases available for new nodes from %d to %d
data.cause: All the currently available leases are being used.\nHence the number of leases available are increased.
data.action: None\n

data.message: Failed to save the node number acquired for node %s; Details at %s in %s
data.cause:
CSSD failed to save the node number acquired during startup.
The node number is saved to speed up the subsequent startup.
Hence this is not a real problem but just a performance degradation
on the next startup.
data.action: Collect Clusterware alert log, CSSD logs and OHASD logs indicated\nin the message and contact Oracle Support Services.\n

data.message: CSSD daemon is started in %s mode
data.cause: CSSD has been started on the node.
data.action: None\n

data.message: Unable to discover any voting files, retrying discovery in %d seconds; Details at %s in %s
A failure occurred in the CSS daemon during initialization; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: A fatal error occurred during the initialization of the CSS daemon.
data.action:
Check for prior errors logged in the alert log. Correct any
errors that can be corrected.  If there are no errors shown,
or the errors cannot be resolved, contact Oracle Support
Services

data.message: The CSS daemon cannot join the cluster because the software version %s is lower than the active version %s; Details at %s in %s
data.cause: The cluster has been upgraded to the active version indicated.\nin the message, but this node is at a lower software version,\nas indicated in the message.
data.action: Upgrade this node to the active version indicated in the message\n

data.message: The CSS daemon has detected a voting file add during startup and is waiting for the add to complete; Details at %s in %s
data.cause:
A voting file add started on another node is in progress while
this CSS daemon is starting.  To avoid the potential for data
corruption, the CSS daemon on this node must wait for the add
to complete.
data.action:
This is normally a temporary condition that is automatically
resolved. If the clusterware stack cannot start on any node,
this condition may be corrected by starting the clusterware
stack in exclusive mode using 'crsctl start crs -excl'
followed by 'crsctl stop crs' on one node.  This will
automatically correct the condition and the clusterware can
be started normally on all nodes.

data.message: The CSS daemon is unable to continue due to a failure in required component %s.
data.cause: A component required by the Cluster Synchronization Service\n(CSS) daemon has failed.  The CSS daemon is unable to\ncontinue and is failing.
data.action: See the alert log for more detailed messages indicating the\nnature of the problem and the location of additional\ninformation regarding this error.

data.message: Cluster Synchronization Service daemon (CSSD) %s not scheduled for %d msecs.
data.cause:
Excessive system load has prevented threads in the Cluster
Synchronization Service daemon (CSSD) from being scheduled for
execution for the time indicated in the message. This indicates
the system is overloaded.

data.message: Cluster %s configured with nodes %s.
data.cause: None.
data.action: None.

data.message: Node %s added to cluster.
data.cause: None.
data.action: None.

data.message: Node %s deleted from cluster.
data.cause: None.
data.action: None.

data.message: Node %s upgraded to version %s.
data.cause: None.
data.action: None.

data.message: Unable to connect to the CSS daemon, return code %d
data.cause: Could not initialize the CSS connection.
data.action: Verify that the CSS daemon is running and restart it if it\nis not up.  Retry the operation.

data.message: An error occurred when obtaining the node number of this host, return code %d
data.cause: The request for node number of this node failed.
data.action:
Verify that the CSS daemon is running and restart it if not
Retry the operation that failed after restart.
Look for error messages from the CSS daemon in the alert log
indicating any problems.

data.message: An internal cluster configuration command failed in an OCR/OLR operation. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: This is an internal error.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Node-specific configuration for node %s in Oracle Local Registry was upgraded to version %s.
data.cause: None.
data.action: None.

data.message: The cluster configuration command failed to open OCR or OLR key %s. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: An expected or required piece of configuration is missing from the\ncluster or local registry.
data.action:
Use the ocrcheck utility to detect errors, and the ocrdump utility
to review the registry contents. If problems exist, the registry may
need to be recovered or restored. If the problem persists, contact
Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Node-specific configuration for node %s in Oracle Local Registry was patched to patch level %u.
data.cause: None.
data.action: None.

data.message: Node %s patched to patch level %u.
data.cause: None.

data.message: CRS service setting (%s) is changed from [%s] to [%s].
data.cause: None.
data.action: None.

data.message: memory allocation error when initiating the connection
data.cause: failed to allocate memory for the connection with the target process.
data.action: None.

data.message: Read-only attribute '%s' cannot be modified
data.cause: An attempt was made to modify a read-only attribute.
data.action: None.

data.message: error %d encountered when receiving messages from %s
data.cause: no meta or response message was received from the target process.
data.action: Retry again at a later time.

data.message: invalid component key name <%s> used
data.cause: the given component key name could not be recognized.
data.action: re-run the command with a valid component key name.

data.message: invalid message type <%d> used
data.cause: an unrecognized message type was sent.
data.action: Retry with a valid command again.

data.message: unable to get authentication for user %s
data.cause: current user was not authenticated for connection.
data.action: Log in as another user and try again.

data.message: invalid response message from %s
data.cause: Response message has incorrect format.
data.action: Retry again at a later time.

data.message: no response at index %d in response message from %s
data.cause: Response message did not contain a response at the specified index.
data.action: If this is an unexpected result, retry again at a later time.

data.message: syntax error in command
data.cause: The command syntax is not valid.
data.action: Issue 'crsctl debug -h' to see command syntax details.\nWatch out for ',' vs. ';'.\n

data.message: user %s does not have the required privileges
data.cause: An attempt to make a diagnostic connection to a Clusterware daemon failed\nbecause the user does not have required privileges.
data.action: Use system tools to identify the user of the specified daemon process.\nLog on as the same user as the specified daemon process and try again.

data.message: The OLR was formatted using version %d.
data.cause: Successfully formatted the OLR location(s).
data.action: None.

data.message: The OLR was restored from file %s.
data.cause: The OLR was successfully restored from a backup file as requested\nby the user.
data.action: None.

data.message: The OLR format was downgraded to version %d.
data.cause: The OLR was successfully downgraded to an earlier block format\nas requested by the user.
data.action: None.

data.message: The OLR was imported from %s.
data.cause: Successfully imported the OLR contents from a file.
data.action: None.

data.message: The OLR upgrade was completed. Version has changed from %d to %d. Details in %s.
data.cause: The OLR was successfully upgraded to a newer block format.
data.action: None.

data.message: The OLR location %s is inaccessible. Details in %s.
data.cause: An error occurred while accessing the OLR.
data.action: Use the "ocrcheck -local" command to validate the accessibility of\nthe device and its block integrity. Check that the OLR location in\nquestion has the correct permissions.

data.message: The OLR service started on node %s.
data.cause: The OLR was successfully started.
data.action: None

data.message: Failed to import Oracle Local Registry from file %s
data.cause: Unable to read data from the import file and import to the\nlocal registry
data.action: Check availability of the local registry and the details of the\nfailure from the log file

data.message: The Oracle Local Registry has invalid contents. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: Some of the Oracle Local Registry contents were invalid.
data.action:
Check the log file indicated in the message for more details. Use
the 'ocrcheck -local' command to detect errors, and the
'ocrdump -local' command to review the registry contents. If
problems exist, the registry may need to be recovered or restored.
If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: The Oracle Local Registry backup file %s could not be validated. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: The indicated Oracle Local Registry (OLR) backup file\ncould not be validated due to validation process not starting or\nfailing to run the validation check.
data.action: Re-attempt to backup the Oracle Local Registry (OLR).\nIf the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: GPnP: %s
data.cause: This conveys a message from the GPnP layer to the alert log.
data.action: Look up the imbedded message and respond accordingly.

data.message: Cannot get GPnP profile. Error %s (%s).
data.cause: Get GPnP profile operation failed.

data.message: GPNPD is not running on local node.
data.cause: GPNPD is not running on local node. GPnP request cannot be completed.
data.action: Make sure GPNPD is running and retry the operation.

data.message: GPnP profile signature verification failed. %s request aborted.
data.cause: GPnP profile used in GPnP request or request result does not have a valid signature.
data.action: If error persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: GPnP resource discovery (MDNSD) is not running on local node.
data.cause: GPnP resource discovery failed.
data.action: Make sure resource discovery service (MDNSD) runs on local node.

data.message: GPnP service on host \\"%s\\" not found.
data.cause: Remote GPnP service on requested host were not found in resource discovery results.
data.action: Make sure host is up, clusterware GPnP services (MDNSD and GPNPD) are up and running and network connection is operational.

data.message: No GPnP services on requested remote hosts.
data.cause: GPnP failed to find operational GPnP service on remote host(s).
data.action: Make sure GPnP services (MDNSD and GPNPD) are up and running on remote hosts, and network connection is operational.

data.message: GPnP wallets are either missing or access is denied. Wallet home: %s.
data.cause: Grid Plug and Play(GPnP) failed to open wallets for read operations. Either the GPnP wallets were missing or permission to access them was denied.
data.action: Ensure that the GPnP wallets exist and that read access is permitted.

data.message: Failed to initialize security facility.
data.cause: Error occurred while initializing GPnP security component.
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Failed to initialize Resource Discovery. RD error: %s. Make sure RD providers installed properly.
data.cause: Error occurred while initializing GPnP Resource Discovery (RD).
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Failed to initialize XML Developer's Kit (XDK). XDK error %s.
data.cause: Error occurred while initializing XML Developer's Kit component (XDK).
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Failed to initialize GIPC communication layer. GIPC error: %s.
data.cause: Error occurred while initializing GIPC communication layer.
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Cannot initialize locking subsystem.
data.cause: Error occurred while initializing locking subsystem.
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Failed to initialize GPnP certkey providers.
data.cause: GPnP certkey provider(s) data was not found or corrupt.
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Cannot initialize GPnP, %s (%s).
data.cause: General GPnP initialization failure.
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Cannot get local GPnP security keys (wallet).
data.cause: GPnP wallet(s) directory or files were not found or corrupt.
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: GPNPD is not found.
data.cause: Local GPnP service is not found.
data.action: Make sure GPNPD is running.

data.message: No cluster name found in GPnP profile.
data.cause: Profile is invalid - it must specify a mandatory clustername\nparameter.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: No sequence number found in GPnP profile.
data.cause: Profile is invalid - it must specify a mandatory profile sequence\nparameter.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Flex Cluster mode configuration not found in Grid Plug and Play (GPnP) profile.
data.cause: The Profile did not have Flex Cluster mode configuration and could not be used\nto bring up the stack in Flex Cluster mode.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Cannot get local GPnP profile. Error initializing GPnP profile cache providers.
data.cause: Local GPnP setup was invalid.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Error initializing one of the GPnP profile cache providers.
data.cause: Local GPnP setup was invalid.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Errors occurred while trying to push GPnP profile.
data.cause: GPnP profile update partially failed.
data.action: Try to repeat the update.  If the problem  persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Unable to get GPnP profile from requested cluster nodes.
data.cause: Get GPnP profile from remote nodes failed.
data.action: Try to repeat the update.  If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: GPnP profile is different across cluster nodes. %s.
data.cause: GPnP profile was different across cluster nodes.
data.action: Try to repeat the update.  If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: GPNPD already running on node %s. Terminating.
data.cause: GPnP service instance was already running on node.
data.action: Bring down existing GPNPD instance first.

data.message: GPNPD started on node %s.
data.cause: GPnP service started on node.
data.action: None.

data.message: GPNPD on node %s shut down.
data.cause: GPnP service was shut down by request.
data.action: None.

data.message: GPNPD failed to start listening for GPnP peers.
data.cause: GPnP service failed to open server endpoint.
data.action: Check GPNPD logs for the cause. If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Error getting GPnP profile from \\"%s\\".
data.cause: Get remote GPnP profile from remote node operation failed.
data.action: Retry request. If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Error pushing GPnP profile to \\"%s\\".
data.cause: Push GPnP profile to remote node operation failed.
data.action: Retry request. If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Could not write GPnP profile to local cache.
data.cause: GPNPD service cannot save GPnP profile to local cache.
data.action: Make sure there is at least 10MB of free disk space in Clusterware home. If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Could not delete pending GPnP profile from local cache.
data.cause: GPNPD service cannot delete GPnP profile from local cache.
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Could not write pending GPnP profile to local cache.
data.cause: GPNPD service cannot save GPnP profile to local cache.
data.action: Make sure there is at least 10MB of free disk space in Clusterware home. If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: GPNPD failed get local GPnP profile and cannot continue. Check gpnpd/gpnp client logs.
data.cause: GPnP service cannot find a profile in local cache, and cannot continue.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: GPNPD advertisement with %s succeeded.
data.cause:
Grid Plug and Play Daemon (GPNPD) successfully advertised with
a specified service (for example, Multicast Domain Name Service
Daemon (MDNSD) or Oracle Grid Naming Service (GNS)) previously
failed with CRS-2339.
data.action: None.

data.message: GPNPD advertisement with %s failed. This may block some cluster configuration changes. Advertisement attempts will continue.
data.cause:
Grid Plug and Play Daemon (GPNPD) failed to advertise itself
with a specified service (for example, Multicast Domain Name
Service Daemon (MDNSD) or Oracle Grid Naming Service (GNS)).
Advertisement attempts will continue at regular intervals,
and alerts will periodically be issued.
data.action: Make sure the specified service is running and wait for the success\nmessage CRS-2337 before changing the cluster configuration.

data.message: Errors occurred while processing received gpnp message.
data.cause: Invalid GPnP message received.
data.action: Check gpnp client and GPNPD logs for details. If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: GPNPD on node %s shutting down on signal %d.
data.cause: GPnP service shutting down due to received signal.
data.action: Contact your cluster administrator.

data.message: GPnP messaging received error : %s (%s).
data.cause: GPnP message error received.
data.action: If the problem persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service started on host %s.
data.cause: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service successfully started on the\nlisted node.
data.action: None.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service aborted on host %s. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service aborted due to an internal\nerror. Check the Cluster Time Synchronization Service log file to\ndetermine the cause.
data.action: Determine whether the Cluster Time Synchronization Service has\nauto-started.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service on host %s is in observer mode.
data.cause: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service detected an active vendor time\nsynchronization service on at least one node in the cluster.
data.action:
Oracle Clusterware requires a time synchronization service in active
mode. Oracle Clusterware will work with a vendor service or the Cluster
Time Synchronization Service. If you want to change the Cluster Time
Synchronization Service to active mode, stop and deconfigure the vendor
time synchronization service on all nodes.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service detects that the local time is significantly different from the mean cluster time. Details in %s.
data.cause: The difference between the local time and the time on the reference\nnode was too much to be corrected.
data.action: Shutdown the Oracle Clusterware on the local node. Adjust the\nclock via native platform or OS methods. Restart the Oracle\nClusterware on the local node.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service on host %s is shutdown by user
data.cause: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service on listed node was\nterminated by a user.
data.action: None.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service timed out on host %s. Details in %s.
data.cause: A Cluster Time Synchronization Service action failed. The\ninformation from the reference node was discarded.
data.action:
Verify all network connections between cluster nodes and repair any
problematic connections. If no network problems are found,
1. Run diagcollection.pl.
2. Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: The new Cluster Time Synchronization Service reference node is host %s.
data.cause: A new Cluster Time Synchronization Service reference node has been elected.
data.action: None.

data.message: The clock on host %s has been updated by the Cluster Time Synchronization Service to be synchronous with the mean cluster time.
data.cause: The clock was updated to be in sync with the mean cluster time.
data.action: None.

data.message: The clock on host %s is not synchronous with the mean cluster time. No action has been taken as the Cluster Time Synchronization Service is running in observer mode.
data.cause: The clock was not in sync with the mean cluster time. No action has\nbeen taken as Cluster Time Synchronization Service is running in\nobserver mode.
data.action: Verify correct operation of the vendor time synchronization service\non the node.

data.message: No value is specified
data.cause: There is nothing specified for the value.
data.action: Provide a valid value.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service on host %s is in active mode.
data.cause: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service did not detect an active\nvendor time synchronization service on any node in the cluster.
data.action:
None. If a vendor time synchronization service is preferred to the
Cluster Time Synchronization Service, then configure and start the
vendor time synchronization service on all nodes to change the
Cluster Time Synchronization Service to observer mode.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service will take a long time to perform time synchronization as local time is significantly different from mean cluster time. Details in %s.
data.cause: The difference between the local time and the time on the reference\nnode was too much to be synchronized in a short period.
data.action: (Optional) Shutdown and restart the Oracle Clusterware on this node\nto instantaneously synchronize the time with the reference node.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service detects that the local time is significantly different from the mean cluster time. Details in %s.
data.cause: The difference between the local time and the time on the reference\nnode was too large. No action has been taken as the Cluster Time\nSynchronization Service was running in observer mode.
data.action:
Verify correct operation of the vendor time synchronization service
on the node. Alternatively, if you want to change the Cluster
Time Synchronization Service to active mode, stop and
deconfigure the vendor time synchronization service on all nodes.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service is unable to perform step time synchronization due to high network latency with the reference node. The local time is not significantly different from the mean cluster time. The Cluster Time Synchronization Service is entering slew time synchronization mode.
data.cause:
The Cluster Time Synchronization Service experienced high network
latency. The local time was not significantly different from the
mean cluster time; therefore, the Cluster Time Synchronization
Service will maintain the system time with slew time synchronization.
data.action: Determine the root cause of high network latency, and perform\nappropriate repair if necessary.

data.message: The Cluster Time Synchronization Service is unable to perform step time synchronization due to high network latency with the reference node. The local time is significantly different from the mean cluster time. The Cluster Time Synchronization Service is aborting.
data.cause:
The Cluster Time Synchronization Service experienced high network
latency. The local time was significantly different from the mean
cluster time; therefore, the Cluster Time Synchronization Service is
aborting.
data.action: Shut down the Oracle Clusterware on the local node. Determine the\nroot cause of high network latency. Perform appropriate repair if\nnecessary, then restart the Oracle Clusterware on the local node.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be registered because its owner '%s' is not the same as the Oracle Restart user '%s'.
data.cause: The resource indicated in the message could not be registered because it was owned by a user other than the Oracle Restart user.
data.action: Resubmit as the Oracle Restart user.

data.message: Cannot stop resource '%s' as it is not running
data.cause: A request to stop a resource that is not running was received.
data.action: Check the current state of the resource, it should no\nlonger be running.

data.message: Resource '%s' is disabled
data.cause: The resource is currently disabled and so may not be operated on.
data.action: Enable the resource and re-submit your request.

data.message: Resource '%s' has dependency error because of resource '%s'
data.cause: The attempted operation has failed because of a dependency on the\nspecified resource.
data.action: Ensure that the intended operation is still desired. If so, the\nspecified resource and its state need to be evaluated to decide on\nthe corrective action.

data.message: Resource '%s' is in UNKNOWN state and must be stopped first
data.cause: The resource cannot be acted upon when it is in the UNKNOWN state.
data.action: Stop the resource manually, make sure it is OFFLINE, and then\nre-submit the request.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be placed on any online servers that satisfy its placement policy
data.cause: The resource cannot be placed because of the constrains imposed\nby its placement policy.
data.action: Either change the placement policy of the resource or re-evaluate\nthe request.

data.message: Another operation is being performed on '%s'. Retry later
data.cause: Another operation is being performed on the specified object.
data.action: Typically, waiting and retrying or using a way to queue the\nrequest are the two choices to proceed.

data.message: Operation on '%s' has been cancelled
data.cause: A scheduled or running operation has been cancelled.
data.action: None.

data.message: Unsupported modifier '%s' in dependency '%s'
data.cause: The modifier is not a valid one.
data.action: Check the specification of the dependency, fix the problem indicated,\nand resubmit the request.

data.message: Incomplete specification of dependency '%s'
data.cause: The specification does not have the dependent object specified.
data.action: Check the specification of the dependency, fix the problem indicated,\nand resubmit the request.

data.message: Resource type '%s' used in dependency '%s' does not exist or is not registered
data.cause: The resource type referenced by the dependency specification is not\nfound.
data.action: Check the specification of the dependency, fix the problem indicated,\nand resubmit the request.

data.message: Resource '%s' used in dependency '%s' does not exist or is not registered
data.cause: The resource referenced by the dependency specification is not\nfound.
data.action: Check the specification of the dependency, fix the problem indicated,\nand resubmit the request.

data.message: Attribute '%s' cannot be specified on per-X basis for resource '%s'
data.cause: The specified attribute is specified on per-X basis, which is not\nallowed for this attribute.
data.action: Remove the specification.

data.message: Attribute format for '%s' is invalid in resource '%s'
data.cause: The specification does not follow valid format.
data.action: Correct the specification and re-submit the request.

data.message: Attribute format for '%s' is invalid
data.cause: The specification does not follow valid format.
data.action: Correct the specification and re-submit the request.

data.message: Dependency attribute specification '%s' is invalid in resource '%s'
data.cause: The specification of relations does not follow valid format.
data.action: Correct the specification and re-submit the request.

data.message: Circular dependency found for resource '%s'
data.cause: The resource dependency specification has a circular dependency.
data.action: Circular dependencies are disallowed. Change the profile\nand re-submit.

data.message: Server pool is not specified for resource '%s'
data.cause: The resource profile does not have server pool specified.
data.action: Either specify a an existing server pool or\nHOSTING_MEMBERS in the profile and re-submit the request.

data.message: Required attribute '%s' is not specified for resource '%s'
data.cause: A required attribute is missing from the resource profile.
data.action: Add the attribute to the profile and re-submit the request.

data.message: Either '%s' or '%s' must be specified when '%s' is '%s'
data.cause: Neither or both of the parameters was specified.
data.action: Specify exactly one of the two and re-submit.

data.message: Invalid value '%s' for attribute '%s'
data.cause: The value specified for the attribute is inappropriate or invalid.
data.action: Review the value, correct the problem and re-submit the request.

data.message: Invalid characters are used when specifying the value
data.cause: 1 or more characters used to specify a value are inappropriate.
data.action: Provide a valid value.

data.message: Value specification may only contain '%s'/'%s'/'%s'/'%s'/'%s'/'%s'
data.cause: The value specified is not any of the allowed.
data.action: The value must be one of the allowed ones, as specified. Provide a\nvalid one.

data.message: All instances of the resource '%s' are already running; relocate is not allowed because the force option was not specified
data.cause: All instances of the resource are running and the start request\ndoes not have the force option specified.
data.action: Either specify the force option or re-evaluate the need for the\nrequest.

data.message: There are no available instances of resource '%s' to start on '%s'
data.cause: All instances of the resource are already running or otherwise\nunavailable to be started on the specified server.
data.action: Create more instances or re-evaluate the need for the request.

data.message: Unable to start '%s' because it has a '%s' dependency on '%s'
data.cause: Start/relocate of the resource is impossible because it has a dependency\non another entity which prevents it from being able to start.
data.action: This message will usually be coupled with another one that details\nthe nature of the problem with the other resource. Follow up\non the action recommended for that message.

data.message: Unable to place an instance of '%s' as all possible servers are occupied by the resource
data.cause: Out of possible servers to place the resource on, all already host an instance of the resource.
data.action: You need to add more servers or change the resource placement parameters to allow\nplacement on additional servers.

data.message: Unable to act on '%s' because that would require stopping or relocating '%s', but the force option was not specified
data.cause: Acting on the resource requires stopping or relocating other resources,\nwhich requires that force option be specified, and it is not.
data.action: Re-evaluate the request and if it makes sense, set the force option and\nre-submit.

data.message: Unable to stop '%s' because '%s' has a stop-time '%s' dependency on it
data.cause: Stopping the resource is impossible because it has a dependency\non another resource and there is a problem with that other resource.
data.action: This message will usually be coupled with another one that details\nthe nature of the problem with the other resource. Follow up\non the action recommended for that message.

data.message: Internal error while operating on '%s'
data.cause: General-purpose message for highly unexpected internal errors.
data.action: This message will usually be preceded by another one with a more\nspecific problem description. Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: OCR write failed for '%s'
data.cause: Unknown, but would usually imply corruption or unavailability of the OCR\nor a lack of permissions to update keys or a software defect in the\nOCR code.
data.action: Validate that OCR is accessible, validate that key permissions match.\nContact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Server '%s' is down. Unable to perform the operation on '%s'
data.cause: The server is down and therefore the operation cannot be performed.
data.action: Try using a different server.

data.message: Resource type '%s' is not registered
data.cause: The specified resource type is not registered.
data.action: Re-evaluate the request.

data.message: Resource type '%s' does not have attribute '%s' and thus it cannot be updated
data.action: Re-evaluate the request.

data.message: Required attribute '%s' is not specified for '%s'
data.cause: A required attribute is missing from the entity's profile.
data.action: Add the attribute to the profile and re-submit the request.

data.message: Resource type '%s' cannot be extended directly; use its extensions instead
data.cause: The type cannot be extended.
data.action: Use a type that extends this one.

data.message: Value for attribute '%s' is of incorrect type (string is expected)
data.cause: The type of the value is not correct.
data.action: Re-submit the request with the value specified in proper type.

data.message: A resource with the name '%s' is already registered
data.cause: A resource with specified name is already registered.
data.action: Use a unique name for the new resource.

data.message: Value for attribute '%s' is of incorrect type (integer is expected)
data.cause: The type of the value is not correct.
data.action: Re-submit the request with the value specified in proper type.

data.message: Server pool '%s' is not registered
data.cause: The specified server pool is not registered.
data.action: Re-evaluate the request.

data.message: The tag '%s' is mentioned in both '%s' and '%s' attributes, which is conflicting
data.cause: The same tag is used to specify exclusive as well as overlapping server pools.\nThese requirements cannot be satisfied simultaneously.
data.action: Remove the tag from one of the attributes.

data.message: The type is not specified for attribute '%s'
data.cause: Value type specification is missing for the attribute.
data.action: Specify a proper type and re-submit.

data.message: The name '%s' is longer than the allowed maximum of '%d' characters
data.cause: The name is too long.
data.action: Use a shorter name.

data.message: Cannot operate on '%s'. %s
data.cause: The entity specified is currently locked as part of another operation.
data.action: Re-submit the request later.

data.message: Server '%s' is not online
data.cause: Operation is invalid because the specified server is not online.
data.action: Provide an online server name.

data.message: Update of an internal or read-only attribute '%s' for resource '%s' is not allowed
data.cause: Internal and read-only attributes may not be updated.
data.action: Exclude internal and read-only attributes from your request.

data.message: A cyclical dependency on '%s' is detected from '%s'
data.cause: There is a cycle in the dependency graph. Cycles are disallowed.
data.action: Re-evaluate the dependency graph.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be placed on '%s' as it is not a valid candidate as per the placement policy
data.cause: The resource cannot be placed because of the constrains imposed\nby its placement policy.
data.action: Either change the placement policy of the resource or re-evaluate\nthe request.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be failed-over because it has other non-OFFLINE instances on the server '%s'
data.cause: The resource cannot be failed-over from the specified server because has other\nnon-OFFLINE instances still available on that server and fail-over can only be done\non all instances of the resource on the server as a whole.
data.action: None.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be failed-over because it is of type '%s', which cannot relocate
data.cause: Local resources cannot be relocated from one server to another.
data.action: None.

data.message: There are no available instances of resource '%s' to start.
data.cause: All instances of the resource are in the ONLINE or UNKNOWN state.
data.action: Re-evaluate the need for the request.

data.message: Server pool '%s' cannot be unregistered as it does not exist
data.cause: The server pool you are trying to remove does not exist.
data.action: Make sure the server pool you are trying to remove exists.

data.message: Server pool '%s' cannot be unregistered as it is referenced by resource '%s'
data.cause: The server pool you are trying to remove has references to it.
data.action: Make sure the server pool you are trying to remove is not referenced by other entities.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be relocated as it is a local resource
data.cause: The request is impossible to complete as local resources never relocate.
data.action: Re-evaluate the request.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be restored to its original state after a failed relocate attempt
data.cause: After an unsuccessful attempt to relocate a resource, crsd was unable to restore the resource.
data.action: Manual intervention may be required. Re-try starting the resource.

data.message: Server pool '%s' cannot be unregistered as it is referenced by server pool '%s'
data.cause: The server pool you are trying to remove has references to it.
data.action: Make sure the server pool you are trying to remove is not referenced by other entities.

data.message: Resource type '%s' may not be unregistered as there are types that are based on it.
data.cause: Types may not be unregistered if they have derived types.
data.action: Remove derived types first, then remove this one.

data.message: Resource type '%s' may not be unregistered as it has the following resources:%s
data.cause: Types may not be unregistered if they have resources registered.
data.action: Remove the specified resources first, then remove the type.

data.message: Resource type '%s' does not exist
data.cause: The resource type referenced does not exist.
data.action: Specify a correct type.

data.message: Resource type '%s' may not be unregistered as it is referenced by resource '%s'
data.cause: Types may not be unregistered if they are referenced in resource dependencies.
data.action: Make sure there are no existing resources that reference this type in their dependencies.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be relocated as it is not running
data.cause: Only currently running resources can be relocated.
data.action: Make sure the resource is running before issuing the request.

data.message: Attempt to start resource '%s' on '%s' has failed. Will re-retry on '%s' now.
data.cause: Undirected (no target member) start of a resource has failed for the server; a retry is in progress.
data.action: None, this is an informational message.

data.message: Failed to relocate resource '%s'. Will attempt to restore it on '%s' now.
data.cause: Resource relocate operation was unable to relocate the resource to any of the possible servers.
data.action: None, this is an informational message.

data.message: Attempt to relocate resource '%s' to '%s' has failed. Will re-retry on '%s' now.
data.cause: Undirected (no target member) relocate of a resource has failed for the server; a retry is in progress.
data.action: None, this is an informational message.

data.message: User '%s' does not have sufficient permissions to operate on resource '%s', which is part of the dependency specification.
data.cause: User does not have permissions to operate on the resource as it will prevent the current resource from starting or staying online in future.
data.action:
The user performing the operation must have access
privileges to operate on the entire resource dependency tree. The
user must either be given those privileges by modifying the dependent
resources' access rights or another user having permissions should
perform this operation.

data.message: Error while parsing the default value for attribute '%s'
data.cause: The default value specified is not proper.
data.action: Make sure the value is proper for its type.

data.message: Base resource type name '%s' does not exist
data.cause: The name of a base type used is not valid.
data.action: Use an existing type as a base.

data.message: Unsupported value type is used in attribute '%s'
data.cause: An unsupported value type was specified in the attribute's definition.
data.action: Use one of the supported types.

data.message: Internal Error: Number of objects '%d' is different from number of lists '%d'
data.cause: This is an internal error.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Dependency kind '%s' is specified more than once for resource '%s'
data.cause: A dependency kind is used more than once in the profile of the resource.
data.action: Combine multiple specifications of the same dependency kind into a single clause.

data.message: '%s' is not a supported Special Value
data.cause: The specified identifier is not a valid Special Value.
data.action: Check the value for correctness.

data.message: ACL entry for owner field is missing.
data.cause: The complete value for the ACL attribute has been provided but it is missing a mandatory entry specifying permissions for the owner.
data.action: Include permissions for the owner in the value of ACL attribute.

data.message: ACL entry for primary group field is missing.
data.cause: The complete value for the ACL attribute has been provided but it is missing a mandatory entry specifying permissions for the primary group.
data.action: Include permissions for the primary in the value of ACL attribute.

data.message: ACL entry for users other than the owner and those belonging to primary group is missing.
data.cause: The ACL attribute is missing a mandatory entry specifying permissions for users other than the owner and those belonging to the primary group.
data.action: Include permissions for other users in the value of ACL attribute.

data.message: User '%s' is not a member of group '%s'
data.cause: The group that the caller claims to be a member of has no such user by configuration.
data.action: Make sure the group is configured to have the calling user as a member.

data.message: Use of '%s' in attributes and values is not allowed
data.cause: A disallowed character was detected.
data.action: Retry without the disallowed character.

data.message: Value of '%s' (%d) may not be greater than that of '%s' (%d)
data.cause: The specified values do not make sense - one may not be less than the other.
data.action: Use valid values.

data.message: Value '%d' may not be less than '%d'
data.cause: The value is less than the allowed minimum.
data.action: Use a proper value.

data.message: Value '%d' is neither '%d' nor '%d'
data.cause: The value must be one of the two and it is neither.
data.action: Use a proper value.

data.message: Value '%s' is not any of the following '%s', '%s', '%s'
data.cause: The value must be one of the ones specified and it is not.
data.action: Use a proper value.

data.message: Value '%s' does not follow expected format: <n>[s|d|m|w|h]
data.cause: The value specification does not follow required format.
data.action: Use a proper value.

data.message: Value '%d' must be in the '%d' - '%d' range
data.cause: The value is not within the allowed range.
data.action: Use a proper value.

data.message: Value '%s' is not allowed here
data.cause: The value is not proper in this context.
data.action: Use a proper value.

data.message: Deletion of built-in resource types is not allowed
data.cause: An attempt was made to delete a built-in resource type.
data.action: Removal of built-in types is not allowed.

data.message: Deletion of a running resource '%s' requires the force option
data.cause: An attempt was made to delete a resource that is still running.
data.action: Stop the resource first using the 'crsctl stop resource' command.\nIf the resource cannot be stopped, specify the force option to the 'crsctl delete' command.

data.message: Attribute '%s' is internal and thus may not be overridden in type '%s'
data.cause: Attributes defined in built-in resource types that are\ninternal to the subsystem may never be overridden in user-defined\nresource types.
data.action: Do not specify this attribute in the new user-defined type.

data.message: A cyclical dependency on '%s' is detected from '%s' via type '%s'
data.cause: There is a cycle in the dependency graph, via a resource type. Cycles are disallowed.
data.action: Re-evaluate the dependency graph.

data.message: Relation modifier '%s' is invalid for relation kind '%s'
data.cause: An unexpected relation modifier is specified.
data.action: Use defined modifiers only.

data.message: The name '%s' contains the following invalid characters: '%s'
A resource name may not be empty or contain spaces
data.cause: A name must not be empty or contain space character(s).
data.action: Specify a valid name.

data.message: A server pool name may not be empty or contain spaces
data.cause: A name must not be empty or contain space character(s).
data.action: Specify a valid name.

data.message: A type name may not be empty or contain spaces
data.cause: A name must not be empty or contain space character(s).
data.action: Specify a valid name.

data.message: Comparator value '%s' in the filter specification is not supported
data.cause: An unsupported comparator was supplied.
data.action: Use a supported value.

data.message: Filter specification '%s' is invalid
data.cause: The filter specification invalid or empty.
data.action: Provide a valid filter or do not specify you have one.

data.message: Server pool '%s' has already been registered
data.cause: A server pool with this name has already been registered.
data.action: Provide a name that is not currently in use.

data.message: Modifications to the '%s' attribute of server pools are not supported
data.cause: Changes to the value of the attribute are not allowed.
data.action: Create a different pool with the desired value and use it.

data.message: Server '%s' may not be moved to pool '%s'
data.cause: Because of one or more of configuration-related constrains, the move of\nthe server is not a valid operation at the time.
data.action: Re-evaluate the request's validity in the context\nof the entire error stack.

data.message: Server pool '%s' is already at its maximum size of '%d'
data.cause: The pool is already at the maximum.
data.action: The request is impossible to execute.

data.message: Server '%s' is not in a parent pool of '%s'
data.cause: The server is not in a parent pool of the pool in question.
data.action: The request is impossible to execute.

data.message: Server '%s' is already in another top-level server pool
data.cause: The server is already consumed by a different top-level\npool and all such pools are exclusive as far as server ownership.
data.action: The request is impossible to execute.

data.message: Server '%s' is not explicitly mentioned as a candidate by server pool '%s'
data.cause: The server is not in the list of names the pool allows\nas candidates.
data.action: Use a server that is in the specified group.

data.message: Server '%s' is in server pool '%s' which is exclusive with server pool '%s'
data.cause: The server is already in a pool that's configured to be\nexclusive with the one at hand.
data.action: The request is impossible to execute.

data.message: Server '%s' cannot be assigned to server pool '%s' because it is not a top-level pool
data.cause: Server movement is only supported between top-level server pools.
data.action: The request is impossible to execute as such an action is\nnot supported.

data.message: Server '%s' is already assigned to server pool '%s'
data.cause: Server movement makes no sense: the server is already in the target pool.
data.action: Check the request validity.

data.message: Server '%s' cannot be relocated from server pool '%s' because the pool disallows transfers
data.cause: The server pool is configured not to allow server transfers.
data.action: Check the request validity.

data.message: Server '%s' may not be relocated from server pool '%s' because it is not above its minimum size
data.cause: Server pools of identical or higher importance may not be used\nto steal servers from if they\nare not above their minimum size.
data.action: Update the configuration of server pools by either\nchanging the importance or the minimum size or both and then\nre-submit the request.

data.message: Attribute '%s' has not been specified on per-X basis for resource '%s'
data.cause: The specified attribute has not been specified on per-X basis for\nthis resource.
data.action: Check the per-X attribute for the resource, fix and resubmit.

data.message: Attribute '%s' is not a per-X value and cannot be removed
data.cause: The specified attribute is not a per-X value.
data.action: Check the per-X attribute for the resource, fix and resubmit.

data.message: Server '%s' may not be relocated to server pool '%s' as the pool disallows transfers
data.cause: The server pool is configured not to allow server transfers.
data.action: Check the request validity.

data.message: Server '%s' is unavailable
data.cause: The server is not available at the moment.
data.action: Check available servers and rerun the request with an active server.

data.message: Server pool '%s' is built-in and may not be deleted
data.cause: Built-in server pools may never be deleted.
data.action: None.

data.message: Server pools do not have attribute named '%s'
data.cause: An unsupported attribute was provided as part of the\nregister or update request.
data.action: Double check the attributes that are supplied.

data.message: Could not find resource '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to operate on a resource that is not\nregistered.
data.action: Check if the resource is registered.

data.message: Could not find resource type '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to operate on a resource type that is not\nregistered.
data.action: Check if the resource type is registered.

data.message: Could not find server pool '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to operate on a server pool that is not\nregistered.
data.action: Check if the server pool is registered.

data.message: The owner of resource type '%s' does not have sufficient permissions to operate on resource type '%s', from which it is directly or indirectly derived.
data.cause:
Update of a resource type in the current manner is not
allowed as it will severely limit operations on the current
resource type and will potentially prevent resources of derived
types from starting or staying online in future.
data.action: If access privileges must be changed, then they need to\nchanged bottom-up in a dependency.

data.message: Incorrect value of attribute flags has been specified for attribute %s. Only READONLY flag can be changed for a type attribute.
data.cause: Attempt was made to update the flag on a resource type\nattribute. The only change allowed is to the readonly property of\nthe attribute.
data.action: Provide correct value of the attribute flag.

data.message: Cannot change data type %s of existing attribute %s to type %s.
data.cause: Attempt was made to update the data type of attribute value.
data.action: Data type of the attribute cannot be changed.

data.message: Server pool '%s' may not be edited
data.cause: The pool's attributes may not be edited.
data.action: None.

data.message: Attribute '%s' of server pool '%s' may not be edited
data.cause: Editing of the attribute of the server pool is not allowed.
data.action: None.

data.message: Server '%s' is assigned to '%s' to which you have no permission. The operation is not authorized.
data.cause:
The operation requires making the specified server a
placement candidate for the resources owned by the requesting user.
However, this is not allowed because the user is not authorized to
utilize the server.
data.action: Either specify another server that that's in the pool you\nare authorized to use or request that a cluster administrator gives you access to the\npool to which the server is currently assigned.

data.message: Server '%s' is not assigned to any server pool and thus may only be specified by a cluster administrator
data.cause:
The operation makes use of the server that's not currently
assigned to a server pool and the requesting user is not a cluster
administrator. Because of that use of the server cannot be
authorized at the moment.
data.action: Either request a cluster administrator to perform the\noperation for you or wait until the server has joined the cluster\nand is assigned to a pool to which you have an x-permission.

data.message: Server pool '%s' cannot accept server '%s' because its name is not specified in '%s'
data.cause: Only servers whose names are mentioned in the attribute may\nbe assigned to the pool.
data.action: None.

data.message: One of '%s', '%s' must be specified when '%s' is '%s'
data.cause: Neither of the parameters was specified.
data.action: Specify either of the two and re-submit.

data.message: Owner of resource '%s' does not have execute permission to pool '%s' and may not use it
data.cause: Resource profile references a server pool to which the\nowner of the resource does not have the X-permission.
data.action: Either have the pool's permission changed appropriately or\nuse a different pool.

data.message: Owner of server pool '%s' does not have execute permission to parent server pool '%s'
data.cause: Parent pool does not have the X-permission for the pool's parent.
data.action: Either have the desired parent pool's permission changed\nappropriately or use a different pool.

data.message: You must have execute permission on pool '%s' to relocate server '%s'
data.cause: The client requesting the operation does not have proper\npermissions to the specified pool.
data.action: Acquire required permissions or use another server/pool.\nPermissions can be added by an authorized user using 'crsctl setperm'\ncommand.

data.message: Server pool '%s' may not be a parent of itself
data.cause: An attempt was made to make a server pool a parent of itself.
data.action: Re-evaluate the server pool dependencies.

data.message: Only cluster administrators are allowed to create top-level server pools
data.cause: An attempt was made to create a server pool that has no parent pools.\nCreation of such pools is only allowed for cluster administrators.
data.action: Either acquire the role of cluster administrator or have one create\nthe pool for you.

data.message: Only cluster administrators are allowed to create local resources
data.cause: An attempt was made to create a local resource which is only\nallowed for cluster administrators.
data.action: Either acquire the role of cluster administrator or have\none create the resource for you.

data.message: Only cluster administrators are allowed to create cluster resources that may run anywhere in the cluster
data.cause: An attempt was made to create a cluster resource that may\nrun anywhere in the cluster which is only for cluster administrators.
data.action: Either acquire the role of cluster administrator or have\none create the resource for you.

data.message: There are no more servers to try to place resource '%s' on that would satisfy its placement policy
data.cause: After one or more attempts, the system ran out of servers\nthat can be used to place the resource and satisfy its placement\npolicy.
data.action: None.

data.message: Required resource '%s' is missing.
data.cause: A resource that's configured as required is not registered.
data.action: Register the missing resource or update the dependency\nspecification so as to the missing resource is not required for\nstart.

data.message: The value of '%s' cannot override that defined in the resource's type: '%s'
data.cause: Agent filename cannot be overridden on per-resource basis.
data.action: Define a sub-type that uses the agent. Then create a\nresource of this new type.

data.message: Relocate resource is not a valid command for this configuration
data.cause: A relocate command was issued in the configuration where it is not possible in principle.
data.action: None.

data.message: The server pool(s) where resource '%s' could run have no servers
data.cause: All of the server pools the resource uses (and has permissions to use) have no servers assigned.
data.action: Either make sure there are active servers in the pools or\nuse different pools for the resource.

data.message: No hosting members of '%s' are either online or are allowed to be used by the resource
data.cause: No server out of the enumerated as hosting members is\nonline or, if it is, may be used by the resource.
data.action: You need to either add more servers into the cluster or\nrequest permission to pools to which currently available servers\nare assigned.

data.message: Cannot create resources of type '%s'
data.cause: The type is abstract.
data.action: Only concrete extensions of the type can be created.

data.message: '%s' must have a default value if specified
data.cause: This attribute must have a default value if specified.
data.action: Modify the type definition so that the attribute is\nremoved or has a valid default value.

data.message: Attribute '%s' may not be a negative value
data.cause: A negative value was provided for an attribute which only\naccepts non-negative values.
data.action: Specify a non-negative number.

data.message: Configuration of resource '%s' prevents it from starting on any online servers.
data.cause: An attempt was made to start a resource, but the resource configuration prevented it from starting.
data.action: Check resource configuration.

data.message: Attribute '%s' of '%s' is internally managed and may not be specified
data.cause: An internal attribute was specified as part of an add/modify request.
data.action: Re-execute the request without any internal attribute.

data.message: Resource '%s' is configured to run only on '%s' and cannot be started on '%s'
data.cause: An attempt was made to start a resource on a server where\nit cannot run given its placement configuration.
data.action: Make sure you start resources where they are configured to run.

data.message: Resource alias '%s' must use special values to be unique for each server
data.cause: Resource alias name must resolve to a unique identifier for\nevery server in the cluster. To achieve that, special values that yield\ndifferent values on for each server must be used.
data.action: You need to special an alias with special variables that\nwill make it unique for every server.

data.message: %s is a resource and only resource instances can be relocated.
data.cause: An attempt was made to relocate a resource.
data.action: Make sure you supply a resource instance rather than a resource.

data.message: Special value evaluation must be associated with a resource instance
data.cause: Because some special values are per-server, each special value\nevaluation request must be associated with a resource instance.
data.action: Specify a server for the resource using -k or -n.

data.message: Resource '%s' or all of its instances are disabled
data.cause: This is an API return code for requests that cannot be\nperformed because the resource is disabled.
data.action: Look at the detailed error messages that should\nalways accompany this error.

data.message: All instances of resource '%s' are disabled
data.cause: All instances of the resource instances are disabled.
data.action: In order to change a resource state through CRS, its\ninstances need to be enabled.

data.message: Resource '%s' is disabled on server '%s'
data.cause: The resource was disabled on the specified server.
data.action: Either re-enable, or use a different server.

data.message: Resource instance of '%s' with %s=%d, %s=%d is disabled
data.cause: The resource instance whose cardinality/degree is specified\nis disabled.
data.action: Either re-enable or use a different resource instance.

data.message: Resource '%s' is already running on '%s'
data.cause: The resource is already running everywhere it may run.
data.action: None.

data.message: Resource '%s' is disabled on '%s'
data.cause: The resource is disabled on every server it is configured\nto start on.
data.action: None.

data.message: Resource '%s' is disabled on '%s' and is already running on '%s'
data.cause: The resource is disabled on every server it is configured\nto start on.
data.action: None.

data.message: This message reserved for crsctl enable cluster online help
Resource '%s' with %s=%s may only run on servers assigned to %s and %s, both of which are empty
data.cause: The resource's placement policy only allows it to run on\nservers assigned to the specified pools, and they are all empty.
data.action: Either change the placement policy of the resource, or\nchange the cluster configuration so that there are servers in those\npools.

data.message: The value of attribute '%s' (%d) may not not be above '%d'
data.cause: Attribute value specified is above the allowed maximum.
data.action: Use a value below the specified maximum.

data.message: The value is out of range. Maximum allowed value is '%d'
data.cause: Attribute value is out of the valid range.
data.action: The value needs to be in a valid range.

data.message: Unable to start/relocate '%s' because '%s' has a stop-time '%s' dependency on it
data.cause: Start/relocate of the resource is impossible because\nanother resource has a stop-time dependency on it and the action\nrequires stopping that resources.
data.action: This message will usually be coupled with another one that details\nthe nature of the problem with the other resource. Follow up\non the action recommended for that message.

data.message: Error processing attribute '%s': %s
data.cause: The value specified for the attribute is inappropriate or invalid.
data.action: Review the value, correct the problem and re-submit the request.

data.message: Attempting to start '%s' on '%s'
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: None.

data.message: Attempting to stop '%s' on '%s'
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: None.

data.message: Start of '%s' on '%s' failed
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: None.

data.message: Stop of '%s' on '%s' failed
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: None.

data.message: Start of '%s' on '%s' succeeded
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: None.

data.message: Stop of '%s' on '%s' succeeded
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: None.

data.message: '%s' on '%s' has experienced an unrecoverable failure
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: Perform whatever steps necessary to reset the state.

data.message: Attempting to clean '%s' on '%s'
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: None.

data.message: Clean of '%s' on '%s' failed
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: None.

data.message: Clean of '%s' on '%s' succeeded
data.cause: This is a status message.
data.action: None.

data.message: It is locked by '%s' for command '%s' issued from '%s'
data.cause: This message is generated for operations that have a locking conflict.
data.action: None.

data.message: It is locked by '%s' for command '%s'
data.cause: This message is generated for operations that have a locking conflict.
data.action: None.
