data.cause: The specified resources could not be stopped.
data.action: Stop the specified resources manually and retry the last action.

data.message: Cannot stop resource '%s' as it is not running on server '%s'
data.cause: An request to stop a resource on a server where it is not\nrunning was received
data.action: Check the current state of the resource; it should no\nlonger be running on that server.

data.message: Starting shutdown of Cluster Ready Services-managed resources on server '%(1)s'
data.cause: Shutdown of Cluster Ready Services and the resources it manages has started on\nthe specified server.
data.action: None.

data.message: Starting shutdown of Oracle High Availability Services-managed resources on '%s'
data.cause: Shutdown of Oracle High Availability Services and the resources it manages has started on the indicated server.
data.action: None.

data.message: Shutdown of Cluster Ready Services-managed resources on '%s' has completed
data.cause: Shutdown of Cluster Ready Services and the resources it manages on the indicated server has completed.
data.action: None.

data.message: Shutdown of Oracle High Availability Services-managed resources on '%s' has completed
data.cause: Shutdown of Oracle High Availability Services and the resources it manages has completed on the indicated server.
data.action: None.

data.message: Shutdown of Cluster Ready Services-managed resources on '%s' has failed
data.cause: The failure is associated with one or more of the resources affected by this command on the indicated server."
data.action: Error message(s) preceding this one should have the details about the\nresources that refused to shut down. Either manually stop those\nresources or retry with the force option.

data.message: Shutdown of Oracle High Availability Services-managed resources on '%s' has failed
data.cause: The failure is associated with one or more of the resources affected by this command on the indicated server."
data.action: Error message(s) preceding this one should have the details about the\nresources that refused to shut down. Either manually stop those\nresources or retry with the force option.

data.message: The command may not proceed when Cluster Ready Services is not running
data.cause: This command must stop Cluster Ready Services-managed\nresources. However, Cluster Ready Services is not running, which\ndoes not mean its resources are not running.
data.action: The underlying reason for Cluster Ready Services not\nrunning needs to be resolved and the command retried.\nAlternatively, the command can be retried with the force option.

data.message: Shutdown is already in progress for '%s', waiting for it to complete
data.cause: Another shutdown command was issued for the indicated server in the\npast and it is currently in progress. This command will wait until\nthe original command completes and then complete as well.
data.action: None.

data.message: State change received for resource '%s' from unexpected server '%s'. Details at '%s' in '%s'.
data.cause: A state change was reported for an instance of the resource from a server where the resource was never started.
data.action: Shutdown the resource on the unexpected server

data.message: Failed to shut down resource '%s' on '%s'
data.cause: Shut down failed because the listed resource failed to stop.
data.action: Error message(s) preceding this one should have the details about the\nresources that refused to shut down. Either manually stop those\nresources or retry with the force option.

data.message: Cannot start resource '%s' as it is already in the INTERMEDIATE state on server '%s'
data.cause: An attempt was made to start a resource that is already in the INTERMEDIATE state.
data.action: Determine why the resource is in the INTERMEDIATE state based on the value of the STATE_DETAILS\nattribute. If it is due to a check timeout, no action is needed. Otherwise, manual intervention\nis required to bring the resource out of the INTERMEDIATE state.

data.message: No instance of the resource '%s' should be running
data.cause: An attempt was made to relocate resource and the resource's\ninstances to be relocated have TARGET=OFFLINE.
data.action: Restart the resource to change the value of the TARGET attribute to ONLINE.\nExamining the value of the INTERNAL_STATE attribute can be used to determine if the instances\nare being operated on currently.

data.message: Purging events not published within 15 minutes
data.cause: The events could not be published to the Event Manager Daemon either because it is down or there are errors doing the publish.
data.action: Check the status of the Event Manager Daemon.

data.message: Attribute '%s' has already been declared in a derived type '%s'
data.cause:
An attempt was made to add a new attribute definition to a
resource type that has an identically named attribute already
defined in one or more derived types. Attributes declared in base types can be overridden
in derived ones, but the opposite is not allowed.
data.action: Pick a different attribute name or delete the derived\ntype(s), resubmit, and then add derived types back.

data.message: Internal: Server Fencing
'%s' is not a valid attribute of server categories.
data.cause: An attempt was made to set a value for an attribute which does not belong to server categories.
data.action: Use a valid attribute.

data.message: Error retrieving status for entity '%s'. Details can be found in CRS-%d.
Server '%s' is registered.
Unable to start '%s' because it has a '%s' dependency on resource type '%s' and no resource of that type can satisfy the dependency
data.cause: Start/relocate of the resource is impossible because it has a dependency\non a resource type no resource of which can currently be used to satisfy the dependency.
data.action: This message will normally be coupled with one or more other messages that detail\nthe nature of the problem for each existing resource of the type.

data.message: Failed to create stop operation for resource '%s'
data.cause: Creating the stop operation did not complete successfully.
data.action: Error message(s) preceding this one should have more details about the problem.\nTry shutting down the resource manually, or retrying with the force option.

data.message: Resource '%s' failed to start automatically.
data.cause: This message comes up when the automatic start for the resource has\nfailed during a reboot of the cluster node or restart of the clusterware stack.\nSee previous resource specific messages for more details.
data.action: Use 'crsctl start resource' to start the resource manually.

data.message: Update Configuration Policy Set
Failed to update cluster configuration policy set. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: Could not update repository with new configuration data.
data.action: Use the ocrcheck utility to detect errors in OCR. If problems exist, the registry may need to be recovered or restored.

data.message: Cluster configuration policy set is corrupted. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: Could not read the configuration data from the repository.
data.action: Use the ocrcheck utility to detect errors in OCR. If problems exist, the registry may need to be recovered or restored.

data.message: Unregister Server Category
Register Server Category
Modify Server Category
Server category '%s' does not exist.
data.cause: A request was received that referenced a non-existing server category.
data.action: Make sure a registered server category is used.

data.message: Server category '%s' is already registered.
data.cause: A request to register a server category with a duplicate name was received.
data.action: Use a unique name.

data.message: Server category '%s' cannot be unregistered as it is referenced by resource '%s'.
data.cause: The server category you are trying to remove has references to it.
data.action: Make sure the server category you are trying to remove is not referenced by other entities.

data.message: Server category '%s' cannot be unregistered as it is referenced by server pool '%s'.
data.cause: The server category you are trying to remove has references to it.
data.action: Make sure the server category you are trying to remove is not referenced by other entities.

data.message: Failed to delete server category '%s' from repository. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: Could not update repository with server category details.
data.action: Use the ocrcheck utility to detect errors in OCR. If problems exist, the registry may need to be recovered or restored.

data.message: Failed to save server category '%s'. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: Could not update repository with server pool details.
data.action: Use the ocrcheck utility to detect errors in OCR. If problems exist, the registry may need to be recovered or restored.

data.message: Required attribute '%s' is missing for configuration policy '%s'.
data.cause: A required attribute was not specified.
data.action: Make sure the attribute is specified.

data.message: Fatal error while validating configuration policy '%s'.
data.cause: There's a problem with the configuration data in the specified policy.
data.action: This message always follows the actual error description.

data.message: Server pool '%s' is not declared in the policy set.
data.cause: Each configuration policy may only define server pool.\nconfiguration for the pools declared to be a part of the policy set.
data.action: Either remove the server pool from the policy, change its\nname, or extend the policy set to include the pool's name.

data.message: The new active policy name '%s' was not found.
data.cause: An attempt to activate non-existent policy was made.
data.action: Use a registered policy's name instead.

data.message: '%s' is reserved for a built-in configuration policy and cannot be used.
data.cause: This name is reserved for a built-in object.
data.action: Use a different name.

data.message: Configuration policy '%s' already exists.
data.cause: A configuration policy name specified was defined multiple times.
data.action: Make sure each policy is only defined once.

data.message: Server pools cannot be removed from the configuration policy set without activating a new policy at the same time.
data.cause: Server pools can be removed from the configuration policy set only if the command also activates a policy.
data.action: To remove the server pools from the system, activate a new policy with the update. To remove the server pools from the policy control only, resubmit with the -ksp option.

data.message: This policy is built-in and managed automatically to reflect current configuration
Failed to stop resource while attempting CARDINALITY modification
data.cause: An attempt to stop a resource during CARDINALITY modification failed.
data.action: Use 'crsctl stop resource' to stop the resource manually and then retry the update operation.

data.message: Update operation cannot proceed because it would need to stop resources.
data.cause: An update to CARDINALITY would require the operation to stop resources.
data.action: Either manually stop enough resources using 'crsctl stop resource' or specify the force option to have them selected for you.

data.message: A server category name may not be empty or contain spaces.
data.cause: A name must not be empty or contain space character(s).
data.action: Specify a valid name.

data.message: Either '%s' or '%s' may be specified, but never both.
data.cause: Two mutually exclusive attributes were used at the same time, which is not allowed.
data.action: Use either one or the other.

data.message: Server '%s' does not belong to server category '%s' of pool '%s'.
data.action: Use a different server, a different pool, or change the configuration of either the pool or the\ncategory or both.

data.message: Either '%s' or '%s' must be specified, or both.
data.cause: At least one of the two attributes must have a value.
data.action: Specify a value for either or both.

data.message: One of '%s', '%s' or '%s' must be specified when '%s' is '%s'.
data.cause: One attribute of the three is required for this configuration.
data.action: Specify a value for one attribute of the three.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot start on server '%s' as the server does not belong to the resource's server category.
data.cause: This resource may only run on the servers that belong to\nthe server category of the resource.
data.action: Pick a server that belongs to the category.

data.message: When using a server category, the resource must have '%s' attribute set to '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to register a resorce that uses a server\ncategory and yet is not configured to utlize any available server.
data.action: Set the attribute to the required value.

data.message: There are no servers that belong to the server category '%s' of resource '%s'.
data.cause: The resource cannot be started as there are no available servers that belong to its category.
data.action: Add servers to the cluster or change the category to be more inclusive.

data.message: Resource '%s' has been unregistered.
Cluster Ready Services' active version is below required level of '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to use functionality that is only available starting from the specified active version.
data.action: Upgrade to the minimum required version.

data.message: Resource instance '%s' does not exist.
data.cause: A request was received that referenced a nonexistent resource instance.
data.action: Make sure a registered resource instance is used.

data.message: '%s' must be a resource instance.
data.cause: This command may only be issued on a resource instance but the supplied reference was to an\nobject of a different type.
data.action: Use a registered resource instance.

data.message: Action '%s' on resource '%s' timed out.
data.cause: The action did complete within the allotted time.
data.action: None.

data.message: Unable to complete processing of the '%s' action for resource '%s' on server '%s' as Cluster Ready Services is not reachable.
data.cause: The processing of the specified action was aborted because\nCluster Ready Services was no longer reachable.
data.action: Unless the clusterware stack was stopped or the server was\nrebooted, Cluster Ready Services will restart momentarily. The\naction can be retried thereafter.

data.message: Waiting for resource '%s' to start on server '%s'.
data.cause: The resource is now expected to start on the server.
data.action: None.

data.message: Waiting for resource '%s' to stop on server '%s'.
data.cause: The resource is now expected to stop on the server.
data.action: None.

data.message: There is no active action on resource instance '%s'
data.cause: An attempt was made to finish an action on the resource instance while no\ncorresponding attempt to start the action was found or an attempt to start the action was\ntimed out before a request to finish the action arrived.
data.action: Check the state of the resource and re-do the complete\ncycle if needed.

data.message: Authorization failure: OS User '%s' does not exist on server '%s'
data.cause: The specified operating system user does not exist on the specified server. Cluster Ready Services requires that all users used by the resource it manages exist on each server of the cluster.
data.action: Add the specified operating user on the specified server.

data.message: Error while reading resources: Resource: %s . Error: %s  Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: This is an internal error.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Authorization failure:  Resource [ %s ]
data.cause: A resource operation could not be performed because authorization checking failed.
data.action: Check the ownership, group, and permissions associated with the resource and ensure that the associated operating system user and group definitions are consistent on all cluster nodes.

data.message: Start of '%s' on '%s' has been delayed to maintain concurrency limit of %d.
data.cause: The configured concurrent start action limit was reached.
data.action: The start action will automatically resume as soon as possible.

data.message: Stop of '%s' on '%s' has been delayed to maintain concurrency limit of %d.
data.cause: The configured concurrent stop action limit was reached.
data.action: The stop action will automatically resume as soon as possible.

data.message: Conflicting specification of server pool and server.
data.cause: Server pool name and server name were specified in a start command.
data.action: Specify either server pool name or servername, not both.

data.message: Unknown server pool name: '%s' .
data.cause: The server pool name given to start/stop command did not exist.
data.action: Specify a valid server pool name.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be started in a server pool because it is a local resource.
data.cause: A local resource name was given to start/stop command.
data.action: Specify a cluster resource name.

data.message: Resource '%s' is not configured to run in server pool '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to start or stop the resource in a server pool where resource was not configured to run.
data.action: Modify resource's attribute to have this server pool or specify a different resource.

data.message: Unknown names for server pools or for filters.
data.cause: An invalid value was  supplied for the '-s' or '-w' argument in a start/stop command or to the API calls.
data.action: Provide valid server pool names or filter attributes.

data.message: Cannot stop resource '%s' because it is not running in server pool '%s'.
data.cause: A resource stop request specified a server pool on which the resource is not running.
data.action: Check the current state of the resource; it should no\nlonger be running in that server pool.

data.message: User '%s' does not have permission to run action '%s' on resource '%s'.
data.cause: A username and/or group was specified for the action permissions, but the current user is not included in the specification.
data.action: Use 'crsctl modify' to update the ACTIONS attribute for this resource to add the current user to the permission list for this action, or remove all user and group specifications to enable universal access.

data.message: Cannot run action '%s' on resource '%s' because the resource is not online.
data.cause: A resource action operation could not be performed because the resource was not online.
data.action: Ensure the resource is online before attempting to run an action.

data.message: Resource Action
Found no resources to run action on.
Cannot update the ACTIONS attribute, because the input is not valid
data.cause: A resource update operation could not be performed, because the input value is not vvalid.
data.action: Ensure the ACTIONS name attribute is specified in 32 or less US7ASCII characters. Ensure users and groups are prefixed with the appropriate identifier, either "user:" or "group:"

data.message: Cannot restart resource '%s' because it is not running.
data.cause: A resource restart action was not performed because the resource is not running.
data.action: Ensure that the resource which needs to be restarted is up and running.

data.message: Restart Resource
Resource '%s' cannot be started on server '%s' because it has an exclusion dependency with resources of type '%s'.
data.cause: An exclusion dependency was configured without the right to preempt a running resource.
data.action: Pick a different server or stop the other resource(s) on this server.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be started on server '%s' because it has an exclusion dependency with resources of type '%s' and the force option was not specified.
data.cause: An exclusion dependency was configured but the force option was not used to stop the running resource(s).
data.action: Either pick a different server or use the force option.

data.message: Server pool '%s' cannot be added to the policy set.
data.cause: The Generic server pool as well as its sub-pools cannot be\nadded to the policy set.
data.action: Remove the pool from SERVER_POOL_NAMES attribute.

data.message: '%s' is not a valid attribute of configuration policies.
data.cause: An attempt was made to set a value for an attribute which does not belong to configuration policies.
data.action: Use a valid attribute.

data.message: '%s' is not a valid attribute of the policy set.
data.cause: An attempt was made to set a value for an attribute which does not belong to the policy set.
data.action: Use a valid attribute.

data.message: An OCR write operation has failed during upgrade of the object schema.
data.cause: While performing CRS upgrade as part of the clusterware upgrade, an OCR write operation has failed.
data.action: Examine the clusterware alert log for more information about OCR failures.

data.message: Resource group '%s' has been unregistered.
Resource '%s' cannot be started on server '%s' because it has an exclusion dependency with resource '%s'.
data.cause: An exclusion dependency was configured between the two resources without the right to preempt a running resource.
data.action: Pick a different server or stop the other resource on this server.

data.message: Resource '%s' cannot be started on server '%s' because it has an exclusion dependency with resource '%s' and the force option is not used.
data.cause: An exclusion dependency was configured between the two resources but the force option was not used to stop the running resource.
data.action: Either pick a different server or use the force option.

data.message: Cluster Ready Services Autostart
Could not restart resource '%s' on server '%s'.
data.cause: A required part of restart operation has failed.
data.action: Check the preceding errors to see the cause and take appropriate action.

data.message: Failed to record shutdown information in OLR.
data.cause: An attempt to record information during a normal shutdown failed. This will cause the shutdown to be regarded as unplanned on the next startup, and may lead to some driver resources being disabled.
data.action: Use the ocrconfig and ocrcheck utilities to detect errors in OCR. If problems exist, the registry may need to be recovered or restored.

data.message: Disabled resource '%s' due to OHASD crashes
data.cause: OHASD crashes have exceeded the autostart thresholds set for this resource, and the resource has been disabled as a result.
data.action: Use crsctl config to look up whether a resource has been disabled, and crsctl enable/disable to manually change the status.

data.message: Owner '%s' of the entity '%s' does not belong to the '%s' group.
data.cause: The owner of an entity being configured was not a member of the required group.
data.action: The user, issuing the command, needs to be configured to be in the group.

data.message: Failed to restart resource '%s'
data.cause: An attempt to start the resource has failed.
data.action: If failover is not enabled, try manually starting the resource on a different server. If failover is enabled, the resource has been failed over, and any problems are reported in subsequent messages.

data.message: Cannot update the ALERT_TEMPLATE attribute, because the input is not valid
data.cause: A resource update operation could not be performed, because the input value is not valid.
data.action: Ensure that valid attributes are specified in a space separated list.

data.message: Incorrect specification of dependency '%s', only one modifier may be specified.
data.cause: During resource update, an exclusion dependency specified more than the maximum of one modifier.
data.action: Check the specification of the dependency, fix the problem indicated,\nand resubmit the request.

data.message: Additional exclusion dependency discovered on resource '%s' within the same dependency tree.
data.cause: During resource update, a dependency specified more than the maximum of one exclusion per hard dependency tree.
data.action: Check the specification of the dependency, fix the problem indicated,\nand resubmit the request.

data.message: Unable to place an instance of resource '%s' due to an exclusion dependency on '%s'.
data.cause: The resource cannot be placed because of the constraints imposed\nby its start dependencies.
data.action: Either change the resource start dependencies or re-evaluate the request.

data.message: Resource '%s' failed during Clusterware stack start.
data.cause: During Clusterware startup, automatic startup of the indicated resource\nsucceeded but the resource failed before Clusterware startup completed.
data.action: Retry starting Clusterware.

data.message: Server '%s' cannot be used for resource placement currently.
data.cause: The server is currently configured such that it cannot be\nused for resource placement.
data.action: Use a different server.

data.message: cannot stop the last server in Domain Service Cluster with active member cluster named '%s'
data.cause: An attempt to stop the last server in the Domain Service Cluster\nwas rejected because this cluster was still serving the indicated\nclient cluster and perhaps other member clusters."
data.action: Stop the active member clusters that use this Domain Service Cluster\nfirst, or specify the '-f' option."

data.message: An administrator-managed database cannot be configured on a non-Hub server '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to register a database on a\nserver whose role is not 'hub' or the node is currently down.
data.action: Use only online servers configured as Hub servers.

data.message: Policy-managed databases can only be configured in server pools that use '%s' category.
data.cause: An attempt was made to configure a database using a server\npool that does not currently use a category that includes only nodes with the specified role.
data.action: Either use an existing server pool that uses such a category\nor create and use a server pool with such category.

data.message: In order to use '%s' in resources of '%s' type, '%s' must be set to '%s' and '%s' must be set to '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to use an attribute such that other attributes must be set to specific values.
data.action: Resubmit with the mentioned attributes set to the mentioned values.

data.message: Cannot stop ASM instance on server '%s' because it is the only instance running.
data.cause: An attempt was made to stop the last ASM instance in the cluster, which would lead to a complete cluster outage.
data.action: Reissue the request when there are at least two ASM instances running in the cluster.

data.message: Cannot stop the ASM resource because it will lead to a complete cluster outage.
data.cause: An attempt was made to stop all ASM instances in the cluster, which would lead to a complete cluster outage.
data.action: Reissue the request by specifying a concrete node name.

data.message: DEGREE attribute is desupported.
data.cause: An attempt was made to add a resource with DEGREE attribute.
data.action: Remove the DEGREE attribute from the add command.

data.message: User '%s' does not exist on node '%s'.
data.action: Reissue the command with a known username. Or create the user on\nthe node(s) specified, and reissue the command.

data.message: Not authorized to modify the CRS Administrator list.
data.action: Either acquire the role of cluster administrator or have one modify\nthe CRS Administrator list for you.

data.message: Add CRS Administrator
Delete CRS Administrator
Parameter '%s' for 'relocate' is not a singleton resource.
data.cause: A relocate request  specified a resource that is not singleton.
data.action: Specify a singleton resource or a filter that resolves to an\ninstance of  the resource.

data.message: Server pools in a policy do not have ACL attribute
data.cause: A 'crsctl modify serverpool' command specified an ACL attribute with -policy or -all_policies.
data.action: Omit ACL from the attributes.

data.message: Server category '%s' cannot be unregistered as it is referenced by server pool '%s' in policy '%s'.
data.cause: The server category you are trying to remove has references to it in a policy.
data.action: Make sure the server category you are trying to remove is not referenced by other entities in the policy.

data.message: Resource '%s' is not completely configured, and hence cannot be operated upon.
data.cause: A request was made without specifying the PID_FILES or EXECUTABLE_NAMES.
data.action: Specify a value for PID_FILES and/or EXECUTABLE_NAMES attribute, or specify\nvalues for STOP_PROGRAM, CHECK_PROGRAM and CLEAN_PROGRAMS attributes.\n2908 no longer used

data.message: Resource '%s' has been registered.
Server '%s' cannot be assigned to server pool '%s' because its current role is not '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to assign a server to the server pool that did not have the specified role.\nOnly servers with the specified role can be assigned to this server pool.
data.action: Retry using a different server.

data.message: Unable to register server category '%s' as this will affect running resources, but the force option was not specified.
data.cause: One or more running resources were affected by the operation.
data.action: Add more servers to the cluster, stop or relocate the\nresources mentioned right before this error, or use the force option for the same command.

data.message: Unable to modify server category '%s' as this will affect running resources, but the force option was not specified.
data.cause: One or more running resources were affected by the operation.
data.action: Add more servers to the cluster, stop or relocate the\nresources mentioned right before this error, or use the force option for the same command.

data.message: Unable to start resource '%s' on server '%s' because resource dependencies require stopping it on a different server.
data.cause: A start request failed because resource dependencies would require stopping the\nresource in order to start it somewhere else.
data.action: Manually stop the resource before starting it elsewhere.

data.message: 'autostart delay' value '%s' is invalid.
data.cause: The command specified an 'autostart delay' time that was non-numeric or negative.
data.action: Specify a non-negative numeric value for the 'autostart delay' argument.

data.message: 'autostart servercount' value '%s' is invalid.
data.cause: The command specified an 'autostart servercount' value that was non-numeric or negative.
data.action: Specify a positive numeric value for the 'autostart servercount' argument.

data.message: Failed to update 'autostart delay' (%s) or 'autostart servercount' (%s). Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: A request to update the automatic start details failed because of incorrect input values.
data.action: Use the ocrcheck utility to detect errors in OCR. If problems exist, the registry may need to be recovered or restored.

data.message: Set 'CRS Autostart'
The '%s' server pool cannot be removed from the system.
data.cause: The command to remove the server pool from the policy set\nwould have caused it to be removed from the system completely.
data.action: Reissue the 'crsctl modify policyset' command with the -ksp option.

data.message: Authorization failure: operating system group '%s' does not exist on server '%s'
data.cause: The specified operating system group does not exist on the specified server. Cluster Ready Services requires that all groups used by the resources it manages exist on each server of the cluster.
data.action: Add the specified operating system group on the specified server.

data.message: Resource '%s' has no instances to act upon.
data.cause: An attempt was made to act on a resource that has no\nresource instances because it is configured to run on servers that\nhave never existed in the cluster.
data.action: Retry the command when the resource has instances.

data.message: Unable to activate policy '%s' because this will affect running resources, but the force option was not specified.
data.cause: An attempt to activate a new policy would have affected one or more running resources but the force option was not specified.
data.action: Reevaluate the request and if it makes sense, set the force option and\nresubmit.

data.message: Unable to register policy because attribute '%s' for resource '%s' does not have the POLICY_CONFIG flag.
data.cause: An attempt was made to specify resource attributes in the policy that do not have the POLICY_CONFIG flag.
data.action: Only attributes that can be policy managed and have the POLICY_CONFIG flag can be specified in a policy definition.

data.message: The attribute '%s' is not supported for resource type '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt to update a CRS resource specified an attribute that is not associated with the resource type.
data.action: Specify only attributes that are associated with the type of resource being updated.

data.message: The EXPRESSION attribute cannot accept '%s' as a server configuration attribute.
data.cause: An attempt was made to set a server configuration attribute that cannot be used with the EXPRESSION attribute.
data.action: Use a valid attribute.

data.message: The EXPRESSION attribute contains invalid value '%s' for server configuration attribute '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt was made to set a value which cannot be assigned to a server configuration attribute.
data.action: Use a valid value.

data.message: The dependency modification '%s' for the targets '%s' has an unknown dependency or incorrect syntax.
data.cause: An attempt was made to modify an existing dependency without providing a known dependency or the correct modification syntax.
data.action: Refer to the Oracle Clusterware documentation for an explanation of supported dependencies and the resource dependency modification syntax.

data.message: Cannot find a match for target '%s' in the modification list for dependency '%s'.
data.cause: There was no existing dependency that had the same target to be modified.
data.action: Supply the correct target for the dependency modification.

data.message: The requested action for the resource '%s' was aborted due to a timeout.
data.cause: The timeout specified for a custom action was reached before the action could complete.
data.action: Revise the timeout setting and retry the action.

data.message: The dependency on type '%s' cannot be accepted because it is specified multiple times.
data.cause: A duplicate type was assigned as a dependency to a resource.
data.action: Revise the dependency list to ensure that no duplicate types exist.

data.message: The dependency on resource '%s' cannot be accepted because it is specified multiple times.
data.cause: A duplicate resource was assigned as a dependency to a resource.
data.action: Revise the dependency list to ensure that no duplicate resources exist.

data.message: The server category '%s' cannot be deleted because it is still a dependency for one or more resources.
data.cause: An attempt was made to delete a server category that was still a dependency for one or more resources.
data.action: Either modify the dependency attributes of the associated resources or delete those resources and try again.

data.message: Server category '%s' used in dependency '%s' does not exist or is not registered.
data.cause: An attempt was made for the current resource to have a dependency on a server category that does not exist.
data.action: Check the specification of the dependency, fix the problem indicated, and resubmit the request.

data.message: The dependency on server category '%s' is not supported for a resource type.
data.cause: An attempt to specify a server category dependency for a resource type failed because server category dependency is only supported for a resource.
data.action: Omit the server category dependency.

data.message: The server category name for the relation '%s' is missing.
data.cause: The server category name was expected for the resource dependency, but it was not supplied.
data.action: Provide the server category name when resubmitting the request.

data.message: Value '%s' is neither '%s' nor '%s'
The value can be either '%s' or '%s'.
The user manually disabled HAIP.
Resource group '%s' has been registered.
Resource '%s' has been modified.
Resource group '%s' has been modified.
The dispersion dependency '%s' is specified with mutliple modifiers.
data.cause: An attempt to specify the dispersion dependency failed because multiple modifiers were specified where at most one is supported.
data.action: Check the specification of the dependency, fix the problem indicated, and resubmit the request.\n

data.message: Consistency problem in registry while processing category '%s'. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: This is an internal error.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Consistency problem in registry while processing server pool '%s'. Details at %s in %s.
data.cause: This is an internal error.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Consistency check for all entities managed by the Cluster Ready Services has completed successfully.
data.cause: None.
data.action: None.

data.message: cannot run resource '%(1)s' on server '%(2)s' because the server needs an additional %(3)d MB of memory
data.cause: An attempt to start a resource on a server failed because the server\nneeded the indicated additional memory to satisfy the memory\nrequirements of the resource.
data.action:
Change the placement policy of the resource to expand the server
selections, change the memory requirement of the resource, or add
more memory to the server to which the resource is directly
assigned.

data.message: cannot run resource '%(1)s' on server '%(2)s' because the server needs %(3)d additional CPUs
data.cause: An attempt to start a resource on a server failed because the server\nneeded additional CPUs to satisfy the CPU requirement of the\nresource.
data.action: Change the placement policy of the resource to expand the server\nselections, change the CPU requirement of the resource, or add more\nCPUs to the server to which the resource is directly assigned.

data.message: There are no servers satisfying the placement policy for resource '%s'.
data.cause: An attempt to start a resource on servers that were available\naccording to the placement policy failed because none of those\nservers could satisfy the requirements of the resource.
data.action: Change the placement policy of the resource to expand the server\nselections, change the requirements of the resource, or upgrade the\nconfigurations of the eliminated servers.

data.message: Resource instance '%s' is unable to start because it is scheduled for deletion.
data.cause: An online relocate attempt on this resource failed to stop the specified\nresource instance. The resource instance is scheduled for deletion when\nit stops.
data.action: Use 'crsctl stop resource' to stop the resource instance manually.

data.message: authorization failure updating attribute '%s'
data.cause: Write access permission was not granted to this user to modify the attribute.
data.action: Either omit the attribute, or issue the command from an operating system\nuser who has the required permission.

data.message: cannot add resource '%s' because a resource group exists with the same name
data.cause: An attempt to add a resource failed because a resource group with\nthe same name was already registered.
data.action: Reissue the command specifying a different name for the new resource.

data.message: Value '%s' is invalid, must be one of: '%s', '%s', '%s', or '%s'.

stack that is running on the indicated node. The name and number
of the active node may be unknown.

data.message: crsctl start rollingupgrade <version>
Private Network Problem
All OCR locations are on ASM disk groups [%s], and none of these disk groups are mounted. Details are at \\"%s\\" in \\"%s\\".
data.cause:
OCR was configured on ASM disk groups, and all of the listed
disk groups failed to mount.
The possible causes are:
1. A disk was not accessible.
2. A disk  in a normal or high redundancy disk group failed after the
most recent dismount.
3. The ASM_DISKSTRING in the SPFILE or the GPnP profile was incorrect.
data.action:
Check the ASM alert logs for more information.
To correct disk access or failure issues either:
a) restore access to the disks in the disk group and mount
the disk group (via ASMCMD or SQL).
or
b) Issue a force mount to the disk group to offline missing
disks and mount a normal or high redundancy disk group.
To correct the ASM_DISKSTRING in the SPFILE and propagate the
change to the GPnP profile, in sqlplus, issue the SQL command
"ALTER SYSTEM SET ASM_DISKSTRING <discovery_string> ...", see
Setting Oracle ASM Initialization Parameters in the
Automatic Storage Management Administrator's Guide

data.message: An I/O control request to determine whether Infiniband ACLs are enabled failed with error: '%s'.
data.cause: During listener start, an OS 'ioctl' request failed.
data.action: Examine the accompanying error message, resolve the problem reported, and restart the listener.

data.message: Socket creation for communication failed with error: '%s'.
data.cause: During listener start, an OS system call 'socket' failed.
data.action: Examine the accompanying error message, resolve the problem reported, and restart the listener.

data.message: Failed to get required resources
data.cause: There was an internal error while evaluating the required\nresources for the subject resource.
data.action: Contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Reader farm service '%(1)s' does not exist in the PDB '%(2)s' of database '%(3)s'.
data.cause: During the specified reader farm service start or check action, it was found that the service did not exist in the indicated PDB of the indicated database.
data.action: Restart the non-reader farm service of the PDB so that the reader farm service is created in the PDB and then start a reader farm service.

data.message: SCAN listener %s has endpoints registered on incorrect SCAN VIPs.
data.cause: A periodic check by the the listener agent detected that the SCAN listener had endpoints registered on incorrect SCAN VIPs.
data.action: Restart the SCAN listener. If the error persists, contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: Failure communicating with CRS to access a resource profile or perform an action on a resource
data.cause: An attempt to access a resource profile or perform an action on a\nresource encountered an error attempting to communicate with\nOracle Cluster Ready Services (CRS).
data.action: If this error did not occur while bringing the clusterware stack\nup or down, please contact Oracle Support Services. Otherwise,\nretry the operation when the clusterware stack is up.

data.message: The specified entity was not found in the entity list.
data.cause: The Cluster Ready Services daemon was unable to locate the input entity in its entity list.
data.action: Retry the operation after deleting the entity and registering it again.

data.message: The entity is already registered.
data.cause: An attempt was made to register an entity that was already\nregistered.
data.action: If the specification of the entity was incorrect, retry the operation with the correct entity specification.

data.message: The entity is not registered.
data.cause: An attempt was made to operate on an entity that was not registered.
data.action: If the specification of the entity was incorrect, retry specifying the correct entity otherwise register the entity and retry the operation.

data.message: The registration of the entity failed.
data.cause: An attempt to register an entity failed. The preceding error messages provide additional details.
data.action: Correct the issues described in the accompanying error messages and retry the registration.

data.message: Unregistering the entity failed.
data.cause: An attempt to unregister an entity failed. The preceding error messages provide additional details.
data.action: Correct the issues described in the accompanying error messages and try to unregister the entity again.

data.message: The entity failed to start.
data.cause: An attempt to start an entity failed. The preceding error messages provide additional details.
data.action: Correct the issues described in the accompanying error messages and try to start the entity again.

data.message: The entity failed to stop.
data.cause: An attempt to stop an entity failed. The preceding error messages provide additional details.
data.action: Correct the issues described in the accompanying error messages and try to stop the entity again.

data.message: The entity failed to relocate.
data.cause: An attempt to relocate an entity failed. The preceding error messages provide additional details.
data.action: Correct the issues described in the accompanying error messages and try to relocate the entity again.

data.message: The status code is invalid.
data.cause: The status code was not of the type enum CLSCRS_STAT.
data.action: Verify that the status code argument is a valid code returned from the CLSCRS API and retry.

data.message: The entity failed to update.
data.cause: An attempt to update an entity failed. The preceding error messages provide additional details.
data.action: Correct the issues described in the accompanying error messages and try to update the entity again.

data.message: The entity has an invalid profile.
data.cause: There were invalid attributes in the entity profile.
data.action: Check the entity profile, remove any invalid attributes and retry the operation.

data.message: The action script of the entity cannot be found.
data.cause: The action script of the entity specified by the attribute ACTION_SCRIPT could not be located.
data.action: Ensure that the attribute ACTION_SCRIPT exists and specifies a valid script for the entity.

data.message: The entity has a dependency error.
data.cause: An attempt to operate on an entity failed because of the resulting effect on one or more dependent entities. Preceding messages provide details on the nature of the problem.
data.action: Take the corrective action as suggested by the preceding messages and resubmit the operation.

data.message: A placement error was encountered while attempting to operate on the entity.
data.cause: Based on the placement policy for the entity, there was no\navailable server to which the entity could failover or start.
data.action: Check the target server for the entity and restart the entity\nusing the 'crsctl start' command.

data.message: The specified server is not in the cluster.
data.cause: The specified server name did not designate a server in the cluster.
data.action: Check the server names in the cluster and retry the operation specifying a server that is a member of the cluster.

data.message: The operation on the entity has been cancelled.
data.cause: A scheduled or running operation was cancelled.
data.action: None.

data.message: An internal error occurred while operating on the entity.
data.cause: There was an internal error. This message will be preceded by another message with a more specific problem description.
data.action: Review the accompanying error messages and contact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: The entity or all of its instances are disabled.
data.cause: The attempted request could not be serviced because the entity was disabled.
data.action: Enable the entity and retry the operation.

data.message: The active version of Cluster Ready Services is below the required level.
data.cause: An attempt was made to use the functionality that has only been available beginning with the active version specified in the preceding message.
data.action: Upgrade to the minimum required version stated in the preceding message.

data.message: The requested action for the entity was aborted due to a timeout.
data.cause: The timeout specified for a custom action was reached before the action could complete.
data.action: Revise the timeout setting and retry the action.

data.message: The operation cannot be completed due to invalid arguments.
data.cause: Invalid arguments were specified to execute the CRS command.
data.action: Check the arguments and specify only valid arguments to the command.

data.message: The entity could not be registered due to a type mismatch.
data.cause: The registration of an entity failed because the input entity type to the API did not match the type of the entity to be registered.
data.action: Specify the correct entity type to register the entity.

data.message: The resource validity check failed due to an invalid resource type.
data.cause: The value of the attribute TYPE for the resource was not \\'application\\'.
data.action: Specify the value 'application' for the resource attribute TYPE.

data.message: The entity has one or more attributes missing.
data.cause: The validity check failed to find one or more of the attributes NAME, TYPE or ACTION_SCRIPT for the entity.
data.action: Update the entity to have the missing attributes.

data.message: The action script does not exist for the entity.
data.cause: The validity check on the entity failed to find the file specified in the attribute ACTION_SCRIPT of the entity.
data.action: Provide the full path to an existing file for the attribute ACTION_SCRIPT.

data.message: The entity has invalid hosting servers for the placement policy.
data.cause: Either the attribute HOSTMEM_REQ was not set or was empty for the entity.
data.action: Either set the attribute HOSTMEM_REQ or set the attribute PLACEMENT to 'balanced'.

data.message: The attribute HOSTING_MEMBERS must not be specified for the entity.
data.cause: The attribute HOSTING_MEMBERS was specified for the entity with the balanced placement policy.
data.action: Either unset the attribute HOSTING_MEMBERS or set the entity's placement policy to be 'favored' or 'restricted'.

data.message: The value of the attribute HOSTING_MEMBERS for the entity is invalid.
data.cause: The value of the attribute HOSTING_MEMBERS for the entity contained one or more of the characters: ',', ';' or ':'.
data.action: Remove the invalid characters from the value of the attribute HOSTING_MEMBERS.

data.message: An invalid placement policy was specified for the entity.
data.action: Set the attribute PLACEMENT to either 'favored','restricted', or 'balanced'.

data.message: An invalid value was specified for the attribute AUTO_START.
data.cause: The attribute AUTO_START of the entity was set to an invalid value.
data.action: Set the attribute AUTO_START to either 'always', 'never', or 'restore'.

data.message: One or more attribute of the entity are set to invalid values.
data.cause: An attempt was made to set the attribute to a value of different type.
data.action: Check the attributes and set the value to the appropriate type.

data.message: The entity list is not empty.
data.cause: The entity list passed to receive the information for the queried CRS entities was not empty.
data.action: Create an empty list to pass as the output argument and retry.

data.message: The generated connection key is too long.
data.cause: The size of the environment variables HOST and HOSTNAME were greater than 255 characters.
data.action: Set the environment variables HOST and HOSTNAME to values whose length is no more than 255 characters.\n\n5151 - 5199 : Reserved for CLSCRS-API return code converted to message text.

data.message: Memory could not be allocated.
data.cause: An attempt to allocate memory for an entity failed.
data.action: Check the system logs, correct the condition and retry the operation.

data.message: The pointer to the context is invalid.
data.cause: A null pointer was passed as a pointer to the context.
data.action: Create a valid context and pass its address to the requested operation.

data.message: The entity pointer is invalid.
data.cause: A null pointer was passed to the API for the entity name or the entity value."
data.action: Allocate memory for the entity name and the entity value and pass in the valid pointers to the API.

data.message: The input attribute name not found in the entity's attribute list.
data.cause: An attempt was made to modify a nonexistent attribute of an entity.
data.action: Provide an existing attribute of the entity and retry the operation.

data.message: The end of the entity list was reached.
data.cause: An attempt was made to search beyond the end of the entity list.
data.action: None.

data.message: The entity has no attributes.
data.cause: An attempt was made to get the attribute list for an entity that has no attributes.
data.action: Check the entity name that is being passed. If it's correct then delete the entity, register it with correct attributes and retry the operation.

data.message: The pointer to the operation status message in the entity structure is null.
data.cause: The message pointer in the entity structure was null. The entity maybe corrupted.
data.action: Delete the entity, register the entity and retry the operation.

data.message: The entity list could not be found.
data.cause: An attempt was made to perform an operation on an entity list, but no valid entity list was passed.
data.action: None

data.message: The specified entity already exists.
data.cause: An attempt was made to add an entity that already exists.
data.action: Check the entity name to be added. If it is correct and the existing entity must be recreated, then delete the entity and retry the operation.

data.message: The entity list is empty.
data.cause: The query failed because the entity list was empty.
data.action: Retry the query supplying the intended list of entities.

data.message: The entity name contains invalid characters.
data.cause: An attempted operation was rejected because the specified entity name contained invalid characters.
data.action: Retry the operation specifying a valid entity name.

data.message: The name of a resource or a filter contains invalid characters.
data.cause: An attempted operation was rejected because the specified resource name or the filter name contained invalid characters.
data.action: Retry the operation specifying a valid resource name or the filter name.

data.message: The attribute name is longer than 255 characters.
data.cause: An attempt was made to use an attribute name with a length of more than 255 characters.
data.action: Use an attribute name shorter than 255 characters and retry the operation.

data.message: The supplied buffer is too small for the filter to string conversion.
data.cause: The buffer supplied to the API was too small to hold the output string.
data.action: Increase the buffer size and pass it to the API.

data.message: The specified return code is invalid.

data.action: Verify that the return code argument is a valid code returned from the CLSCRS API and retry.

data.message: The value contains invalid characters.
data.cause: An attempted operation was rejected because the specified attribute name or value contained invalid characters.
data.action: Retry the operation using valid characters.\n

data.message: unable to obtain local host name for reboot advisory log file scan
data.cause: An attempt to retrieve the local host name failed.  The scan\nfor reboot advisory files will not use host name criteria and so\nmay report occurrences for other nodes as well as this one.
data.action: Report this error to Oracle Support Services.

data.message: an error occurred accessing reboot advisory log file location: %s
data.cause:
The scan for reboot advisory log files was unable to access the
indicated file system location.  The location was skipped, so
any reboot advisory files that it contains will not be reported.
This message is accompanied by CLSU- messages containing
details of the access error.
data.action: Respond based on the error described by the accompanying CLSU-\nmessages.  This may involve re-creating the directory or\nchanging its permissions.

data.message: an error occurred searching reboot advisory log file location: %s
data.cause:
The scan for reboot advisory log files was unable to read the next
file name from the indicated file system location.  No further
processing of reboot advisory files from that location occurs.
This message is accompanied by CLSU- messages containing
details of the access error.
data.action: Respond based on the error described by the accompanying CLSU-\nmessages.

data.message: reboot advisory log file: %s is unexpectedly empty
data.cause:
The scan for reboot advisory log files encountered a file that
was empty.  This might happen (rarely) if a component is
initializing its use of reboot advisory at the same time the scan
is running.  Processing of other files in the location continues.
data.action: Frequent occurrence of this message should be reported to\nOracle Support Services.

data.message: an error occurred reading reboot advisory log file: %s
data.cause:
The scan for reboot advisory log files experienced a read error
on a reboot advisory file.  No further processing is done for that
file, but the scan continues with other files.  This message
is accompanied by CLSU- messages containing details of the
read error.
data.action: Respond based on the accompanying CLSU- messages.

data.message: an error occurred closing reboot advisory log file: %s
data.cause:
The scan for reboot advisory log files experienced a close error on
a reboot advisory file.  The scan continues with other files.  This
message is accompanied by CLSU- messages containing details of
the close error.
data.action: Report this error to Oracle Support Services.

data.message: an error occurred opening reboot advisory log file: %s
data.cause:
The scan for reboot advisory log files experienced an error when it
opened a reboot advisory file.  The scan continues with other files.
This message is accompanied by CLSU- messages containing details
of the open error.
data.action: If the error indicated in the accompanying CLSU- messages is one that\ncan be corrected, do so.  Otherwise, report this error to Oracle\nSupport Services.

data.message: an error occurred closing reboot advisory log file location: %s
data.cause:
The scan for reboot advisory log files experienced an error when it
closed the indicated file system location.  Processing of other
reboot advisory locations (if any) continues normally.
This message is accompanied by CLSU- messages containing
details of the close error.
data.action: Report this error to Oracle Support Services.

data.message: %s
data.cause:
Operating system error data related to reboot advisory file
processing was returned.  The error data is packaged in a CLSU- message
that follows "CRS-08008:".  One or more of these messages
appears after a message announcing the error condition.
data.action: Look up the embedded CLSU- message for an explanation of the\noperating system error data.  If there is no CLSU- message ID present,\ncontact Oracle Support Services.

data.message: reboot advisory log file: %s contains invalid data (length %d, error code %d)
data.cause: A reboot advisory log record read from the indicated file contained\nincorrect data.
data.action: Report this error to Oracle Support Services.

data.message: invalid network reboot advisory message detected (length %d, error code %d)
data.cause: A reboot advisory record received over the network was improperly\nformed or contained incorrect data.
data.action: Report this error to Oracle Support Services.

data.message: reboot advisory message from host: %s, component: %s, with time stamp: %s
data.cause:
A reboot advisory message was detected.  During Oracle Clusterware
startup on a given host, messages recently written to disk on that host
before a reset or reboot are detected and announced.  Subsequently,
network reboot advisory messages may be announced as they occur.  These
are reported by hosts other than the one being reset or rebooted.
This message is accompanied by other messages containing details on
what led to the reset or reboot.  The time stamp in this message
begins with either 'U' (denoting UTC time) or 'L' (denoting
local time as viewed by the issuing host).  Note that a given
reset or reboot event can produce multiple occurrences of these
messages on multiple hosts in the cluster.
data.action:
Use the reboot advisory message(s) to determine why Oracle Clusterware
caused a reset or reboot of the affected host, and respond
accordingly.  Refer to the discussion of reboot advisories in the
Oracle Clusterware administration documentation for additional
guidance.

data.message: reboot advisory message from a higher Oracle Clusterware version detected
data.cause:
A reboot advisory message from a higher version installation of
Oracle Clusterware was detected.  This is an expected
occurrence with network reboot advisories when there are nodes with
a higher Oracle Clusterware version than this node (such as during
an upgrade).  It is an unexpected condition with file reboot
advisories.
data.action:

message in a "raw" text form.  In the case of network reboot
advisories, the explanatory message text should be readable and
useful to determine the cause of the node reboot.  If the
reboot advisory message is from a file, report this message to
Oracle Support Services.

data.message: No database name specified for the database argument
data.cause: An 'oclumon' command was issued without a database name.
data.action:
Provide a database name with the 'oclumon' command. Refer to
the product documentation or to the command online help for
information.

data.message: Error %s: Node name is greater than %s bytes
data.cause: An 'oclumon' command was issued with a node name that was too long.
data.action:
Supply a node name no greater than the indicated size with the
'oclumon' command and retry. Refer to the product documentation or
to the command online help for information.

data.message: Model name missing or invalid for the model argument
data.cause: The previous oclumon command was rejected because it did not\ninclude a valid model name.
data.action:
Reissue the oclumon command providing a valid model name. Refer to
the product documentation or to the command online help for
information.

data.message: Server pool name missing or invalid for the server pool argument
data.cause: The previous oclumon command was rejected because it did not\ninclude a valid server pool name.
data.action:
Reissue the oclumon command providing a valid server pool name.
Refer to the product documentation or to the command online help
for information.

data.message: Server pool name specified in a cluster without user-defined server pools
data.cause: The previous oclumon command was rejected because it was issued\nwith a server pool name on a cluster without user-defined server\npools.
data.action:
Reissue the oclumon command without a server pool name. Refer to
the product documentation or to the command online help for
information.

data.message: Node name specified in a cluster with user-defined server pools
data.cause: The previous oclumon command was rejected because it was issued\nwith a node name on a cluster with user-defined server pools.
data.action:
Reissue the oclumon command without a node name. Refer to
the product documentation or to the command online help for
information.

data.message: Parameter '%s' is not supported in combination with parameter '%s'.
data.cause: The command was rejected because the combination of parameters\npassed was invalid.
data.action: Refer to the product documentation or to the online help for the\ncommand and reissue the command with the correct parameters.\n

data.message: Error %s: Parameter '%s' is specified multiple times.
data.cause: The previous 'oclumon' command was rejected because the parameter\nlisted in the message was specified multiple times.
data.action: Refer to the product documentation or to the online help for the\ncommand and reissue the command with the correct parameters.\n

data.message: database name '%s' is invalid
data.cause: An 'oclumon' command was issued with an invalid database name.
data.action:
Provide a valid database name with the 'oclumon' command. Refer to
the product documentation or to the online help for the command
for information.

data.message: No instance of database '%s' is active on this node.
data.cause: The 'oclumon calibrate' command was rejected because no instance\nof the above listed database was active on the local node.
data.action:
Issue the 'srvctl start database' command to start the above listed
database. Issue the 'srvctl status database' command to retrieve
a list of nodes on which the database instances are online. Issue
the 'oclumon calibrate' command again from a node on which the
database instance is online. Refer to the product documentation or
to the online help for the command for information.

data.message: Database '%s' of type '%s' is not supported in a cluster with user-defined server pools.
data.cause: An 'oclumon' command was issued with an administrator-managed\ndatabase in a cluster with user-defined server pools.
data.action:
Reconfigure the database to be policy-managed using the
'srvctl modify database' command to enable monitoring by the Oracle
Cluster Health Analysis service. Verify the monitoring status
using the 'srvctl status cha' command. Re-issue the
'oclumon calibrate' command. Refer to the product documentation or
to the online help for the command for information.

data.message: Error setting Cluster Health Monitor repository size

data.action: Report this error to Oracle Support Services.\n

data.message: Error updating Cluster Health Monitor repository size in configuration file.
data.cause: An error occurred while writing the Cluster Health Monitor repository size to configuration\nfiles.
data.action: Report this error to Oracle Support Services.\n

data.message: No data for the node at the specified time

data.action: This is an informational message only.\n

data.action: Make sure the System Monitor Service is running on the specified node.\n

data.message: No data available for the specified nodes
data.cause: Data was not available for specified nodes.
data.action: Make sure the System Monitor Service is running on the specified nodes.\n

data.message: Internal Error on master
data.cause: An internal error on master caused this error.
data.action: Report this error to Oracle Support Services.\n

data.message: Data requested was outside Cluster Health Monitor retention time limits.
data.cause: A request for data outside Cluster Health Monitor repository limit caused this error.
data.action: Data needs to be requested in the proper Cluster Health Monitor repository limits.\nRefer to the product documentation for more information.\n

data.message: Start time greater than end time
data.cause: A start time greater [or later] than end time caused an error.
data.action: Make sure the start time is less than the end time\nfor the specified range query.\n

data.message: Threshold out of acceptable range
data.cause: A threshold was specified that is outside the allowed range.
data.action: Make sure threshold is within the acceptable range. Refer\ndocumentation or online help for more information\n

data.message: No action required.
LMS busy on peer node
New Cluster Health Monitor repository location same as the old location on node %s

data.cause: The new location specified for Cluster Health Monitor repository does not exist.
data.action: Provide a different location for Cluster Health Monitor repository. Refer\ndocumentation or online help for more information.\n

data.action: Report this error to Oracle Support Services.\n

Cluster Health Monitor repository location change completed on all nodes. Restarting Loggerd.
